exchangeV2.description: The MIB module for informant standard entities.

ex2ADRMSPrelicensingAgent.name: ex2ADRMSPrelicensingAgent
ex2ADRMSPrelicensingAgent.description: Performance counters for Exchange AD RMS Prelicensing Agent

ex2apaAvgProcessTimeLicenseRqst.name: ex2apaAvgProcessTimeLicenseRqst
ex2apaAvgProcessTimeLicenseRqst.description: The Average Processing Time Per License Request (ms) is the average amount of time in milliseconds that it takes the AD RMS Prelicensing agent to process a license.

ex2apaMessageProcessSuccessfully.name: ex2apaMessageProcessSuccessfully
ex2apaMessageProcessSuccessfully.description: Messages Processed Successfully is the total number of protected messages that were successfully processed by the AD RMS Prelicensing agent.

ex2apaPermanentFailLicenseRqsts.name: ex2apaPermanentFailLicenseRqsts
ex2apaPermanentFailLicenseRqsts.description: Permanent Failure License Requests is the total number of license requests that were made by the AD RMS Prelicensing agent and resulted in permanent failures.

ex2apaSuccessfulLicenseRequests.name: ex2apaSuccessfulLicenseRequests
ex2apaSuccessfulLicenseRequests.description: Successful License Requests is the total number of successful license requests that were made by the AD RMS Prelicensing agent.

ex2apaTotalLicenseRequests.name: ex2apaTotalLicenseRequests
ex2apaTotalLicenseRequests.description: Total License Requests is the total number of license requests that were made by the AD RMS Prelicensing agent.

ex2apaTotalLicenseRqstsProcTime.name: ex2apaTotalLicenseRqstsProcTime
ex2apaTotalLicenseRqstsProcTime.description: Total License Requests Processing Time (ms) is the total time spent on license requests by the AD RMS Prelicensing agent in milliseconds.

ex2apaTotalLicenseRequestsPerSec.name: ex2apaTotalLicenseRequestsPerSec
ex2apaTotalLicenseRequestsPerSec.description: Total License Requests/sec is the total number of license requests that were made by the AD RMS Prelicensing agent per second.

ex2apaTotalMessages.name: ex2apaTotalMessages
ex2apaTotalMessages.description: Total Messages is the total number of protected messages that were processed by the AD RMS Prelicensing agent.

ex2apaTotalRecipients.name: ex2apaTotalRecipients
ex2apaTotalRecipients.description: Total Recipients is the total number of recipients from all protected e-mails that were processed by the AD RMS Prelicensing agent.

ex2ADAccessCachesTable.name: ex2ADAccessCachesTable
ex2ADAccessCachesTable.description: One instance per Cache Instance: global Cache Instance data.

ex2ADAccessCachesEntry.name: ex2ADAccessCachesEntry
ex2ADAccessCachesEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'MSExchange ADAccess Caches' object.

ex2aacCacheExpireTotalConfigData.name: ex2aacCacheExpireTotalConfigData
ex2aacCacheExpireTotalConfigData.description: Cache Expiries Total (Configuration Data) is the total number of configuration data objects expired from the cache since system initialization.

ex2aacCacheExpiriesTotalUserData.name: ex2aacCacheExpiriesTotalUserData
ex2aacCacheExpiriesTotalUserData.description: Cache Expiries Total (User Data) is the total number of user data objects expired from the cache since system initialization.

ex2aacCacheExpiriesSecConfigData.name: ex2aacCacheExpiriesSecConfigData
ex2aacCacheExpiriesSecConfigData.description: Cache Expiries/Sec (Configuration Data) is the number of configuration data objects expired from the cache per second.

ex2aacCacheExpirePerSecUserData.name: ex2aacCacheExpirePerSecUserData
ex2aacCacheExpirePerSecUserData.description: Cache Expiries/Sec (User Data) is the number of user data objects expired from the cache per second.

ex2aacCacheHitsTotal.name: ex2aacCacheHitsTotal
ex2aacCacheHitsTotal.description: Cache Hits Total is the total number of 'object found in cache' events since system initialization.

ex2aacCacheHitsPerSec.name: ex2aacCacheHitsPerSec
ex2aacCacheHitsPerSec.description: Cache Hits/Sec is the number of 'object found in cache' events per second.

ex2aacCacheInsertTotalConfigData.name: ex2aacCacheInsertTotalConfigData
ex2aacCacheInsertTotalConfigData.description: Cache Inserts Total (Configuration Data) is the total number of configuration data objects inserted into the cache since system initialization.

ex2aacCacheInsertsTotalUserData.name: ex2aacCacheInsertsTotalUserData
ex2aacCacheInsertsTotalUserData.description: Cache Inserts Total (User Data) is the total number of user data objects inserted into the cache since system initialization.

ex2aacCacheInsertSecConfigurData.name: ex2aacCacheInsertSecConfigurData
ex2aacCacheInsertSecConfigurData.description: Cache Inserts/Sec (Configuration Data) is the number of configuration data objects inserted into the cache per second.

ex2aacCacheInsertsPerSecUserData.name: ex2aacCacheInsertsPerSecUserData
ex2aacCacheInsertsPerSecUserData.description: Cache Inserts/Sec (User Data) is the number of user data objects inserted into the cache per second.

ex2aacCacheMissesTotal.name: ex2aacCacheMissesTotal
ex2aacCacheMissesTotal.description: Cache Misses Total is the total number of 'object not found in cache' events since system initialization.

ex2aacCacheMissesPerSec.name: ex2aacCacheMissesPerSec
ex2aacCacheMissesPerSec.description: Cache Misses/Sec is the number of 'object not found in cache' events per second.

ex2aacDNEntriesConfigurationData.name: ex2aacDNEntriesConfigurationData
ex2aacDNEntriesConfigurationData.description: DN Entries (Configuration Data) is the total number of configuration data DN object type entries in the cache.

ex2aacDNEntriesUserData.name: ex2aacDNEntriesUserData
ex2aacDNEntriesUserData.description: DN Entries (User Data) is the total number of user data DN object type entries in the cache.

ex2aacDNEntriesMemoryConfigData.name: ex2aacDNEntriesMemoryConfigData
ex2aacDNEntriesMemoryConfigData.description: DN Entries Memory (Configuration Data) is the memory occupied by all configuration data DN Entries in the cache (in bytes)

ex2aacDNEntriesMemoryUserData.name: ex2aacDNEntriesMemoryUserData
ex2aacDNEntriesMemoryUserData.description: DN Entries Memory (User Data) is the memory occupied by all user data DN Entries in the cache (in bytes)

ex2aacLDAPSearchesTotal.name: ex2aacLDAPSearchesTotal
ex2aacLDAPSearchesTotal.description: LDAP Searches Total is the total number of LDAP search requests issued since system initialization.

ex2aacLDAPSearchesPerSec.name: ex2aacLDAPSearchesPerSec
ex2aacLDAPSearchesPerSec.description: LDAP Searches/Sec is the number of LDAP search requests issued per second.

ex2aacNotFndDNEntriesConfigData.name: ex2aacNotFndDNEntriesConfigData
ex2aacNotFndDNEntriesConfigData.description: Not Found DN Entries (Configuration Data) is the total number of configuration data 'Not Found DN' type entries in the cache.

ex2aacNotFoundDNEntriesUserData.name: ex2aacNotFoundDNEntriesUserData
ex2aacNotFoundDNEntriesUserData.description: Not Found DN Entries (User Data) is the total number of user data 'Not Found DN' type entries in the cache.

ex2aacNotFndDNEntryMemConfigData.name: ex2aacNotFndDNEntryMemConfigData
ex2aacNotFndDNEntryMemConfigData.description: Not Found DN Entries Memory (Configuration Data) is the memory occupied by all configuration data 'Not Found DN' Entries in the cache (in bytes)

ex2aacNotFndDNEntriesMemUserData.name: ex2aacNotFndDNEntriesMemUserData
ex2aacNotFndDNEntriesMemUserData.description: Not Found DN Entries Memory (User Data) is the memory occupied by all user data 'Not Found DN' Entries in the cache (in bytes)

ex2aacNotFndGUIDEntryConfigData.name: ex2aacNotFndGUIDEntryConfigData
ex2aacNotFndGUIDEntryConfigData.description: Not Found GUID Entries (Configuration Data) is the total number of configuration data 'Not Found GUID' type entries in the cache.

ex2aacNotFndGUIDEntriesUserData.name: ex2aacNotFndGUIDEntriesUserData
ex2aacNotFndGUIDEntriesUserData.description: Not Found GUID Entries (User Data) is the total number of user data 'Not Found GUID' type entries in the cache.

ex2aacNotFndGUIDEntryMemConfigDa.name: ex2aacNotFndGUIDEntryMemConfigDa
ex2aacNotFndGUIDEntryMemConfigDa.description: Not Found GUID Entries Memory (Configuration Data) is the memory occupied by all configuration data 'Not Found GUID' Entries in the cache (in bytes)

ex2aacNotFndGUIDEntryMemUserData.name: ex2aacNotFndGUIDEntryMemUserData
ex2aacNotFndGUIDEntryMemUserData.description: Not Found GUID Entries Memory (User Data) is the memory occupied by all user data 'Not Found GUID' Entries in the cache (in bytes)

ex2aacOutstandingAsyncNotifies.name: ex2aacOutstandingAsyncNotifies
ex2aacOutstandingAsyncNotifies.description: Outstanding Async Notifies is the number of outstanding ldap notification requests.

ex2aacOutstandingAsyncReads.name: ex2aacOutstandingAsyncReads
ex2aacOutstandingAsyncReads.description: Outstanding Async Reads is the number of outstanding ldap read requests.

ex2aacOutstandingAsyncSearches.name: ex2aacOutstandingAsyncSearches
ex2aacOutstandingAsyncSearches.description: Outstanding Async Searches is the number of outstanding ldap search requests.

ex2aacSearchEntriesConfigData.name: ex2aacSearchEntriesConfigData
ex2aacSearchEntriesConfigData.description: Search Entries (Configuration Data) is the total number of configuration data search type entries in the cache.

ex2aacSearchEntriesUserData.name: ex2aacSearchEntriesUserData
ex2aacSearchEntriesUserData.description: Search Entries (User Data) is the total number of user data search type entries in the cache.

ex2aacSearchEntriesMemConfigData.name: ex2aacSearchEntriesMemConfigData
ex2aacSearchEntriesMemConfigData.description: Search Entries Memory (Configuration Data) is the memory occupied by all configuration data search entries in the cache (in bytes)

ex2aacSearchEntryMemoryUserData.name: ex2aacSearchEntryMemoryUserData
ex2aacSearchEntryMemoryUserData.description: Search Entries Memory (User Data) is the memory occupied by all user data search entries in the cache (in bytes)

ex2aacTotalEntriesConfigData.name: ex2aacTotalEntriesConfigData
ex2aacTotalEntriesConfigData.description: Total Entries (Configuration Data) is the total number of configuration data entries in the cache. This includes 'DN', 'Search', 'Not Found DN' and 'Not Found GUID' type entries.

ex2aacTotalEntriesUserData.name: ex2aacTotalEntriesUserData
ex2aacTotalEntriesUserData.description: Total Entries (User Data) is the total number of user data entries in the cache. This includes 'DN', 'Search', 'Not Found DN' and 'Not Found GUID' type entries.

ex2aacTotalEntriesMemConfigData.name: ex2aacTotalEntriesMemConfigData
ex2aacTotalEntriesMemConfigData.description: Total Entries Memory (Configuration Data) is the memory occupied by all configuration data entry objects in the cache (in bytes).

ex2aacTotalEntriesMemoryUserData.name: ex2aacTotalEntriesMemoryUserData
ex2aacTotalEntriesMemoryUserData.description: Total Entries Memory (User Data) is the memory occupied by all user data entry objects in the cache (in bytes).

ex2ADAccessDomainControllerTable.name: ex2ADAccessDomainControllerTable
ex2ADAccessDomainControllerTable.description: One instance per Domain Controller: cross-process Domain Controller data.

ex2ADAccessDomainControllerEntry.name: ex2ADAccessDomainControllerEntry
ex2ADAccessDomainControllerEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'MSExchange ADAccess Domain Controllers' object.

ex2aadcBindFailuresPerMinute.name: ex2aadcBindFailuresPerMinute
ex2aadcBindFailuresPerMinute.description: Bind failures per minute is the number of LDAP bind calls failed during the last minute

ex2aadcCriticalDataFlag.name: ex2aadcCriticalDataFlag
ex2aadcCriticalDataFlag.description: Critical Data flag is 1 if the DC contains the Exchange server account, 0 otherwise

ex2aadcDsGetDcNameElapsedTime.name: ex2aadcDsGetDcNameElapsedTime
ex2aadcDsGetDcNameElapsedTime.description: DsGetDcName elapsed time is the total time (in ms) spent in DsGetDcName call to the DC

ex2aadcGCCapableFlag.name: ex2aadcGCCapableFlag
ex2aadcGCCapableFlag.description: GC capable flag is 1 if the DC is also a GC, 0 otherwise

ex2aadcIsSynchronizedFlag.name: ex2aadcIsSynchronizedFlag
ex2aadcIsSynchronizedFlag.description: IsSynchronized flag is 1 if the DC is synchronized, 0 otherwise

ex2aadcKerberosTicketLifetime.name: ex2aadcKerberosTicketLifetime
ex2aadcKerberosTicketLifetime.description: Kerberos ticket lifetime (in seconds) is an average life time of the last 16 connections closed due to Kerberos ticket expiration

ex2aadcLDAPDisconnectsPerMinute.name: ex2aadcLDAPDisconnectsPerMinute
ex2aadcLDAPDisconnectsPerMinute.description: LDAP Disconnects per minute is the number of LDAP errors that caused Exchange Active Directory Provider to mark the DC down during the last minute

ex2aadcLDAPFatalErrorsPerMinute.name: ex2aadcLDAPFatalErrorsPerMinute
ex2aadcLDAPFatalErrorsPerMinute.description: LDAP Fatal errors per minute is the number of LDAP errors that caused Exchange Active Directory Provider to close the LDAP connection without marking the DC down during the last minute

ex2aadcLDAPPagesPerSec.name: ex2aadcLDAPPagesPerSec
ex2aadcLDAPPagesPerSec.description: LDAP Pages/Sec is the number of additional pages that are retrieved from this DC per second

ex2aadcLDAPReadTime.name: ex2aadcLDAPReadTime
ex2aadcLDAPReadTime.description: LDAP Read Time for a given DC is the time (in ms) taken to send an LDAP read request to the specified DC and receive a response

ex2aadcLDAPReadCallsPerSec.name: ex2aadcLDAPReadCallsPerSec
ex2aadcLDAPReadCallsPerSec.description: LDAP Read calls/Sec is the number of Depth 0 LDAP search calls made by this process per second

ex2aadcLDAPSearchTime.name: ex2aadcLDAPSearchTime
ex2aadcLDAPSearchTime.description: LDAP Search Time is the time (in ms) taken to send an LDAP search request and receive a response

ex2aadcLDAPSearchCallsPerSec.name: ex2aadcLDAPSearchCallsPerSec
ex2aadcLDAPSearchCallsPerSec.description: LDAP Search calls/Sec is the number of Depth 1 or 2 LDAP Search calls made by this process per second

ex2aadcLDAPSearchTimedOutPerMin.name: ex2aadcLDAPSearchTimedOutPerMin
ex2aadcLDAPSearchTimedOutPerMin.description: LDAP Searches timed out per minute is the number of LDAP searches returned LDAP_TIMEOUT during the last minute

ex2aadcLDAPVLVRequestsPerSec.name: ex2aadcLDAPVLVRequestsPerSec
ex2aadcLDAPVLVRequestsPerSec.description: LDAP VLV Requests/Sec is the number of Virtual List View requests made to this DC per second. Usually they are used for Addressbook browse functionality in OWA.

ex2aadcLDAPConnectionLifetime.name: ex2aadcLDAPConnectionLifetime
ex2aadcLDAPConnectionLifetime.description: LDAP connection lifetime (in seconds) is an average life time of the last 16 connections closed (excludes ones closed due to Kerberos ticket expiration)

ex2aadcLocalSiteFlag.name: ex2aadcLocalSiteFlag
ex2aadcLocalSiteFlag.description: Local site flag is 1 if the DC belongs to the local site, 0 otherwise

ex2aadcLongRunningLDAPOperPerMin.name: ex2aadcLongRunningLDAPOperPerMin
ex2aadcLongRunningLDAPOperPerMin.description: Long running LDAP operations/Min is the number of LDAP operations on this DC that took longer than the specified threshold per minute (default threshold is 15 seconds)

ex2aadcNetlogonFlag.name: ex2aadcNetlogonFlag
ex2aadcNetlogonFlag.description: Netlogon flag is 1 when DsGetDcName to the DC succeeds, indicating that NetLogon service is running, 0 otherwise

ex2aadcNumberOfOutstandRequests.name: ex2aadcNumberOfOutstandRequests
ex2aadcNumberOfOutstandRequests.description: Number of outstanding requests is the current number of pending LDAP operations to the DC

ex2aadcOSVersionFlag.name: ex2aadcOSVersionFlag
ex2aadcOSVersionFlag.description: OS Version flag is 1 when the DC satisfies Exchange Active Directory Provider OS/Service Pack requirements, 0 otherwise

ex2aadcPDCFlag.name: ex2aadcPDCFlag
ex2aadcPDCFlag.description: PDC flag is 1if the DC is also a PDC, 0 otherwise

ex2aadcReachabilityBitmask.name: ex2aadcReachabilityBitmask
ex2aadcReachabilityBitmask.description: Reachability bitmask shows how the DC is reachable by using lowest 3 bits for DC, CDC and GC-used ports.

ex2aadcSACLRightFlag.name: ex2aadcSACLRightFlag
ex2aadcSACLRightFlag.description: SACL right flag is 1 if the Exchange server has a SeSecurityPrivilege on the DC, 0 otherwise

ex2aadcUserSearchesFailPerMinute.name: ex2aadcUserSearchesFailPerMinute
ex2aadcUserSearchesFailPerMinute.description: User searches failed per minute is the number of Exchange Active Directory Provider client's searches failed during the last minute

ex2aadcGethostbynameElapsedTime.name: ex2aadcGethostbynameElapsedTime
ex2aadcGethostbynameElapsedTime.description: gethostbyname elapsed time is the total time (in ms) spent in gethostbyname call trying to find the DC's IP address

ex2ADAccessGlobalCounters.name: ex2ADAccessGlobalCounters
ex2ADAccessGlobalCounters.description: MSExchange ADAccess Global Counters contain summary information that is not process or DC specific

ex2aagcDNSQueryDurationTime.name: ex2aagcDNSQueryDurationTime
ex2aagcDNSQueryDurationTime.description: DNS Query duration time shows how long (in ms) the most recent DNSQuery call took

ex2aagcInSiteDomainControllers.name: ex2aagcInSiteDomainControllers
ex2aagcInSiteDomainControllers.description: In-site Domain Controllers is the number of suitable Domain Controllers in the local site

ex2aagcInSiteGlobalCatalogs.name: ex2aagcInSiteGlobalCatalogs
ex2aagcInSiteGlobalCatalogs.description: In-site Global Catalogs is the number of suitable Global Catalogs in the local site

ex2aagcOutOfSiteDomainController.name: ex2aagcOutOfSiteDomainController
ex2aagcOutOfSiteDomainController.description: Out-of-site Domain Controllers is the number of suitable Domain Controllers outside the local site

ex2aagcOutOfSiteGlobalCatalogs.name: ex2aagcOutOfSiteGlobalCatalogs
ex2aagcOutOfSiteGlobalCatalogs.description: Out-of-site Global Catalogs is the number of suitable Global Catalogs outside the local site

ex2aagcTopologyDiscoveryDuraTime.name: ex2aagcTopologyDiscoveryDuraTime
ex2aagcTopologyDiscoveryDuraTime.description: Topology Discovery duration time shows how long (in msec) the most recent Topology discovery took

ex2ADAccessProcessesEntry.name: ex2ADAccessProcessesEntry
ex2ADAccessProcessesEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'MSExchange ADAccess Processes' object.

ex2aapCriticlValidFailuresPerMin.name: ex2aapCriticlValidFailuresPerMin
ex2aapCriticlValidFailuresPerMin.description: Number of critical validation failures (that cause DataValidationException to be thrown) per minute

ex2aapIgnorValidatFailuresPerMin.name: ex2aapIgnorValidatFailuresPerMin
ex2aapIgnorValidatFailuresPerMin.description: Number of non-critical validation failures that cause an object to be removed from the result set per minute

ex2aapLDAPNotFndConfigRdCallSec.name: ex2aapLDAPNotFndConfigRdCallSec
ex2aapLDAPNotFndConfigRdCallSec.description: LDAP Not Found configuration read calls/Sec is the number of Depth 0 LDAP search calls made by this process that failed with 'Not found' per second

ex2aapLDAPPagesPerSec.name: ex2aapLDAPPagesPerSec
ex2aapLDAPPagesPerSec.description: LDAP Pages/Sec is the number of additional pages that are retrieved by this process per second

ex2aapLDAPReadTime.name: ex2aapLDAPReadTime
ex2aapLDAPReadTime.description: LDAP Read Time is the time (in ms) taken to send an LDAP read request and receive a response

ex2aapLDAPReadCallsPerSec.name: ex2aapLDAPReadCallsPerSec
ex2aapLDAPReadCallsPerSec.description: LDAP Read calls/Sec is the number of Depth 0 LDAP search calls made by this process per second

ex2aapLDAPSearchTime.name: ex2aapLDAPSearchTime
ex2aapLDAPSearchTime.description: LDAP Search Time is the time (in ms) taken to send an LDAP search request and receive a response

ex2aapLDAPSearchCallsPerSec.name: ex2aapLDAPSearchCallsPerSec
ex2aapLDAPSearchCallsPerSec.description: LDAP Search calls/Sec is the number of Depth 1 or 2 LDAP Search calls made by this process per second

ex2aapLDAPTimeoutErrorsPerSec.name: ex2aapLDAPTimeoutErrorsPerSec
ex2aapLDAPTimeoutErrorsPerSec.description: LDAP Timeout errors/Sec is the number of LDAP operations made by this process failed because of exceeded Timeout per second

ex2aapLDAPVLVRequestsPerSec.name: ex2aapLDAPVLVRequestsPerSec
ex2aapLDAPVLVRequestsPerSec.description: LDAP VLV requests/Sec is the number of Virtual List View requests made by this process per second. Usually they are used for Addressbook browse functionality in OWA.

ex2aapLDAPWriteTime.name: ex2aapLDAPWriteTime
ex2aapLDAPWriteTime.description: LDAP Write Time is the time (in ms) taken to send an LDAP Add/Modify/Delete request and receive a response

ex2aapLDAPWriteCallsPerSec.name: ex2aapLDAPWriteCallsPerSec
ex2aapLDAPWriteCallsPerSec.description: LDAP Write calls/Sec is the number of LDAP Add/Modify/Delete calls made by this process per second

ex2aapLDAPNotificaReportedPerSec.name: ex2aapLDAPNotificaReportedPerSec
ex2aapLDAPNotificaReportedPerSec.description: LDAP notifications Reported/Sec is the number of LDAP notification results reported by this process to the end users per second

ex2aapLDAPNotificaReceivedPerSec.name: ex2aapLDAPNotificaReceivedPerSec
ex2aapLDAPNotificaReceivedPerSec.description: LDAP notifications received/Sec is the number of LDAP notification results received by this process per second (does not necessarily equal to the number of notifications reported to the end users)

ex2aapLongRunningLDAPOperaPerMin.name: ex2aapLongRunningLDAPOperaPerMin
ex2aapLongRunningLDAPOperaPerMin.description: Long running LDAP operations/Min is the number of LDAP operations made by this process that took longer than the specified threshold per minute (default threshold is 15 seconds)

ex2aapNonCriticalValidFailPerMin.name: ex2aapNonCriticalValidFailPerMin
ex2aapNonCriticalValidFailPerMin.description: Number of non-critical validation failures (that do not cause exceptions) per minute

ex2aapNumberOfOutstandingRequest.name: ex2aapNumberOfOutstandingRequest
ex2aapNumberOfOutstandingRequest.description: Number of outstanding requests is the current number of pending LDAP searches in this process

ex2aapOpenConnectionToDomainCtrl.name: ex2aapOpenConnectionToDomainCtrl
ex2aapOpenConnectionToDomainCtrl.description: Open connections to Domain Controllers in this process

ex2aapOpenConnectionsToGlobalCat.name: ex2aapOpenConnectionsToGlobalCat
ex2aapOpenConnectionsToGlobalCat.description: Open connections to Global Catalogs in this process

ex2aapProcessID.name: ex2aapProcessID
ex2aapProcessID.description: The system Process ID of this process instance

ex2aapTopologyVersion.name: ex2aapTopologyVersion
ex2aapTopologyVersion.description: Current version of the Active Directory topology data used by this process.

ex2asAveragePingTime.name: ex2asAveragePingTime
ex2asAveragePingTime.description: Average Ping Time is the average time elapsed, in milliseconds, waiting for Ping and Hanging Sync requests to complete.

ex2asAverageRequestTime.name: ex2asAverageRequestTime
ex2asAverageRequestTime.description: Average Request Time is the average time elapsed, in milliseconds, waiting for a request to complete.

ex2asBadItemReportGeneratedTotal.name: ex2asBadItemReportGeneratedTotal
ex2asBadItemReportGeneratedTotal.description: Bad Item Reports Generated Total is the total number of bad item reports that were generated since the service was started. This occurs when items fail to convert from the server format to the client format.

ex2asBusyThreads.name: ex2asBusyThreads
ex2asBusyThreads.description: Busy Threads is the number of worker threads that are busy processing requests.

ex2asConflictConcurrentSyncTotal.name: ex2asConflictConcurrentSyncTotal
ex2asConflictConcurrentSyncTotal.description: Conflicting Concurrent Sync Total is the total number of Sync commands which a concurrent sync completed first for the same folder.

ex2asConflictConcurrentSyncPrSec.name: ex2asConflictConcurrentSyncPrSec
ex2asConflictConcurrentSyncPrSec.description: Conflicting Concurrent Sync/sec is the number of Sync commands per second which a concurrent sync completed first for the same folder.

ex2asCreateCollectionCommandsSec.name: ex2asCreateCollectionCommandsSec
ex2asCreateCollectionCommandsSec.description: Create Collection Commands/sec is the number of CreateCollections commands that are processed each second. Clients that are running earlier versions of the ActiveSync protocol use this command to create folders.

ex2asCreateCollectionTotal.name: ex2asCreateCollectionTotal
ex2asCreateCollectionTotal.description: Create Collection Total is the total number of CreateCollection requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asCurrentRequests.name: ex2asCurrentRequests
ex2asCurrentRequests.description: Current Requests is the number of HTTP requests received from ASP.NET.

ex2asDeleteCollectionCommandsSec.name: ex2asDeleteCollectionCommandsSec
ex2asDeleteCollectionCommandsSec.description: Delete Collection Commands/sec is the number of DeleteCollection commands that are processed each second. Clients that are running earlier versions of the ActiveSync protocol use this command to delete folders.

ex2asDeleteCollectionTotal.name: ex2asDeleteCollectionTotal
ex2asDeleteCollectionTotal.description: Delete Collection Total is the total number of DeleteCollections commands that have been processed since the service was started. Clients that are running earlier versions of the Exchange ActiveSync protocol use this command to delete folders.

ex2asDocuLibraryFetchCommandsSec.name: ex2asDocuLibraryFetchCommandsSec
ex2asDocuLibraryFetchCommandsSec.description: Document Library Fetches/sec is the number of DocumentLibrary fetches that are processed each second. This command is used by clients to download Windows SharePoint Services or Windows files shares files.

ex2asDocumentLibraryFetchTotal.name: ex2asDocumentLibraryFetchTotal
ex2asDocumentLibraryFetchTotal.description: Document Library Fetch Total is the total number of DocumentLibrary Fetch requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asDocumentLibrarySearchTotal.name: ex2asDocumentLibrarySearchTotal
ex2asDocumentLibrarySearchTotal.description: Document Library Search Total is the total number of DocumentLibrary Search requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asDocumentLibrarySearchPerSec.name: ex2asDocumentLibrarySearchPerSec
ex2asDocumentLibrarySearchPerSec.description: Document Library Searches Per Second is the number of times per second that clients browse Windows SharePoint Services or Windows file shares items.

ex2asEmptyFolderContentsTotal.name: ex2asEmptyFolderContentsTotal
ex2asEmptyFolderContentsTotal.description: Empty Folder Contents Total is the total number of Empty Folder Contents requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asFailedItemConversionTotal.name: ex2asFailedItemConversionTotal
ex2asFailedItemConversionTotal.description: Failed Item Conversion Total is the total number of items that failed to convert due to modifications made by the server since the service was started.

ex2asFolderCreateCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asFolderCreateCommandsPerSec
ex2asFolderCreateCommandsPerSec.description: Folder Create Commands/sec is the number of FolderCreate commands that are processed each second. Clients use this command to create folders.

ex2asFolderCreateTotal.name: ex2asFolderCreateTotal
ex2asFolderCreateTotal.description: Folder Create Total is the total number of FolderCreate requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asFolderDeleteCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asFolderDeleteCommandsPerSec
ex2asFolderDeleteCommandsPerSec.description: Folder Delete Commands/sec is the number of FolderDelete commands that are processed each second. Clients use this command to delete folders.

ex2asFolderDeleteTotal.name: ex2asFolderDeleteTotal
ex2asFolderDeleteTotal.description: Folder Delete Totals is the total number of FolderDelete commands that have been processed since the service was started. Clients use this command to delete folders.

ex2asFolderSyncCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asFolderSyncCommandsPerSec
ex2asFolderSyncCommandsPerSec.description: Folder Sync Commands/sec is the number of FolderSync commands that are processed each second. Clients use this command to synchronize the folder hierarchy.

ex2asFolderSyncTotal.name: ex2asFolderSyncTotal
ex2asFolderSyncTotal.description: Folder Sync Total is the total number of FolderSync requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asFolderUpdateCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asFolderUpdateCommandsPerSec
ex2asFolderUpdateCommandsPerSec.description: Folder Update Commands/sec is the number of FolderUpdate commands that are processed per second. Clients use this command to rename or move folders.

ex2asFolderUpdateTotal.name: ex2asFolderUpdateTotal
ex2asFolderUpdateTotal.description: Folder Update Total is the total number of FolderUpdate requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asGALSearchTotal.name: ex2asGALSearchTotal
ex2asGALSearchTotal.description: GAL Search Total is the total number of GAL Search requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asGALSearchesPerSec.name: ex2asGALSearchesPerSec
ex2asGALSearchesPerSec.description: GAL Searches/sec is the number of times that the global address list is searched per second.

ex2asGetAttachmentCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asGetAttachmentCommandsPerSec
ex2asGetAttachmentCommandsPerSec.description: Get Attachment Commands/sec is the number of GetAttachment commands that are processed each second. Clients that are running earlier versions of the Exchange ActiveSync protocol use this command to download e-mail attachments.

ex2asGetAttachmentTotal.name: ex2asGetAttachmentTotal
ex2asGetAttachmentTotal.description: Get Attachment Total is the total number of GetAttachments requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asGetHierarchyCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asGetHierarchyCommandsPerSec
ex2asGetHierarchyCommandsPerSec.description: Get Hierarchy Commands/sec is the number of GetHierarchy commands that are processed each second. Clients that are running earlier versions of the ActiveSync protocol use this command to synchronize the folder hierarchy.

ex2asGetHierarchyTotal.name: ex2asGetHierarchyTotal
ex2asGetHierarchyTotal.description: Get Hierarchy Total is the total number of GetHierarchy commands that have been received since the service was started.

ex2asGetItemEstimatCommandPerSec.name: ex2asGetItemEstimatCommandPerSec
ex2asGetItemEstimatCommandPerSec.description: Get Item Estimate Commands/sec is the number of GetItemEstimate commands that are processed each second. The GetItemEstimate command is used by clients to display synchronization progress.

ex2asGetItemEstimateTotal.name: ex2asGetItemEstimateTotal
ex2asGetItemEstimateTotal.description: Get Item Estimate Total is the total number of GetItemEstimate requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asHeartbeatInterval.name: ex2asHeartbeatInterval
ex2asHeartbeatInterval.description: Heartbeat Interval is the heartbeat interval, in seconds, specified by the client that connected most recently.

ex2asIdleThreads.name: ex2asIdleThreads
ex2asIdleThreads.description: Idle Threads is the number of worker threads that are idle.

ex2asIncomingProxyRequestsTotal.name: ex2asIncomingProxyRequestsTotal
ex2asIncomingProxyRequestsTotal.description: Incoming Proxy Requests Total is the total number of HTTP requests received from ASP.NET and proxied to another ActiveSync server since the service was restarted.

ex2asItemOperationsCommandPerSec.name: ex2asItemOperationsCommandPerSec
ex2asItemOperationsCommandPerSec.description: Item Operations Commands/sec is the number of ItemOperations commands that are processed each second.

ex2asItemOperationsTotal.name: ex2asItemOperationsTotal
ex2asItemOperationsTotal.description: Item Operations Total is the total number of ItemOperations requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asMailboxAttchFetchCommandSec.name: ex2asMailboxAttchFetchCommandSec
ex2asMailboxAttchFetchCommandSec.description: Mailbox Attachment Fetch Commands/sec is the number of Mailbox Attachment Fetches that are processed each second.

ex2asMailboxAttachmentFetchTotal.name: ex2asMailboxAttachmentFetchTotal
ex2asMailboxAttachmentFetchTotal.description: Mailbox Attachment Fetch Total is the total number of Mailbox Attachment Fetch commands that have been processed since the service was started. This command is used by clients to download e-mail attachments.

ex2asMailboxItemFetchCommandsSec.name: ex2asMailboxItemFetchCommandsSec
ex2asMailboxItemFetchCommandsSec.description: Number of Mailbox Item Fetches/sec is the number of times that clients download whole Exchange items each second.

ex2asMailboxItemFetchTotal.name: ex2asMailboxItemFetchTotal
ex2asMailboxItemFetchTotal.description: Mailbox Item Fetch Total is the total number of mailbox item fetch requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asMailboxSearchTotal.name: ex2asMailboxSearchTotal
ex2asMailboxSearchTotal.description: Mailbox Search Total is the total number of Mailbox Search requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asMailboxSearchesPerSec.name: ex2asMailboxSearchesPerSec
ex2asMailboxSearchesPerSec.description: Mailbox Searches/sec is the number of times that mailboxes are searched per second.

ex2asMeetingResponsCommandPerSec.name: ex2asMeetingResponsCommandPerSec
ex2asMeetingResponsCommandPerSec.description: Meeting Response Commands/sec is the number of MeetingResponse commands that are processed per second. The client uses this command to designate a meeting as Accepted, Declined, or Tentative.

ex2asMeetingResponseTotal.name: ex2asMeetingResponseTotal
ex2asMeetingResponseTotal.description: Meeting Response Total is the total number of MeetingResponse commands that have been received since the service was started.

ex2asMoveCollectionCommandPerSec.name: ex2asMoveCollectionCommandPerSec
ex2asMoveCollectionCommandPerSec.description: Move Collection Commands/sec is the number of MoveCollection commands that are processed each second. Clients that are running earlier versions of the Exchange ActiveSync protocol use this command to move folders.

ex2asMoveCollectionTotal.name: ex2asMoveCollectionTotal
ex2asMoveCollectionTotal.description: Move Collection Total is the total number of MoveCollections requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asMoveItemsCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asMoveItemsCommandsPerSec
ex2asMoveItemsCommandsPerSec.description: Move Items Commands/sec is the number of MoveItems commands that are processed each second. Clients use this command to move Exchange items between folders.

ex2asMoveItemsTotal.name: ex2asMoveItemsTotal
ex2asMoveItemsTotal.description: Move Items Total is the total number of MoveItems commands that have been received since the service was started.

ex2asNumEmptyFoldrContentProcSec.name: ex2asNumEmptyFoldrContentProcSec
ex2asNumEmptyFoldrContentProcSec.description: Number of Empty Folder Contents Processed/sec is the number of number of Empty Folder commands that are processed each second. This command is used by clients to delete all items in a folder.

ex2asOptionsCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asOptionsCommandsPerSec
ex2asOptionsCommandsPerSec.description: Options Commands/sec is the number of Options commands that are processed each second. Clients can use the Options command to discover the ActiveSync protocol version that is supported by the server.

ex2asOptionsTotal.name: ex2asOptionsTotal
ex2asOptionsTotal.description: Options Total is the total number of options requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asOutgoingProxyRequestsTotal.name: ex2asOutgoingProxyRequestsTotal
ex2asOutgoingProxyRequestsTotal.description: Outgoing Proxy Requests Total is the total number of HTTP requests received by ASP.NET from another ActiveSync server since the service was restarted.

ex2asPID.name: ex2asPID
ex2asPID.description: PID the process ID that is hosting ActiveSync.

ex2asPingCommandsDroppedPerSec.name: ex2asPingCommandsDroppedPerSec
ex2asPingCommandsDroppedPerSec.description: Ping Commands Dropped/sec is the number of Ping commands per second whose connection to the client was dropped before a response could be issued.

ex2asPingCommandsPending.name: ex2asPingCommandsPending
ex2asPingCommandsPending.description: Ping Commands Pending is the number of Ping commands that are currently pending on the server.

ex2asPingCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asPingCommandsPerSec
ex2asPingCommandsPerSec.description: Ping Commands/sec is the number of Ping commands that are processed by the server each second. This command is used to send clients notifications about new e-mail messages or changed items.

ex2asPingDroppedTotal.name: ex2asPingDroppedTotal
ex2asPingDroppedTotal.description: Ping Dropped Total is the total number of Ping commands whose connection to the client was dropped before a response could be issued.

ex2asPingTotal.name: ex2asPingTotal
ex2asPingTotal.description: Ping Total is the total number of Ping commands that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asProvisionCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asProvisionCommandsPerSec
ex2asProvisionCommandsPerSec.description: Provision Commands/sec is the number of Provision commands that are processed each second. The server uses this command to enforce mobile policies.

ex2asProvisionTotal.name: ex2asProvisionTotal
ex2asProvisionTotal.description: Provision Total is the total number of Provision requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asProxyLogonCommandsSentTotal.name: ex2asProxyLogonCommandsSentTotal
ex2asProxyLogonCommandsSentTotal.description: Proxy Logon Commands Sent Total is the total number of proxy logon commands that were sent from this server to another server. This can happen when a user's mailbox is located on an Exchange 2003 server. It can also happen when the Exchange 2007 Client Access server in the same Active Directory site as the user's Mailbox server is not Internet facing.

ex2asProxyLogonReceivedTotal.name: ex2asProxyLogonReceivedTotal
ex2asProxyLogonReceivedTotal.description: Proxy Logon Received Total is the number of ProxyLogon commands that have been received by this server from another server since the service was started.

ex2asRecoverySyncCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asRecoverySyncCommandsPerSec
ex2asRecoverySyncCommandsPerSec.description: Recovery Sync Commands/sec is the number of Recovery Sync requests that are processed each second. The recovery sync process happens to compensate for a failed synchronization with the client.

ex2asRecoverySyncTotal.name: ex2asRecoverySyncTotal
ex2asRecoverySyncTotal.description: Recovery Sync Total is the total number of Recovery Sync requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asRequestsQueued.name: ex2asRequestsQueued
ex2asRequestsQueued.description: Requests Queued is the number of HTTP requests that are waiting to be assigned to a thread.

ex2asRequestsTotal.name: ex2asRequestsTotal
ex2asRequestsTotal.description: Requests Total is the total number of HTTP requests received from ASP.NET since the service was restarted.

ex2asRequestsPerSec.name: ex2asRequestsPerSec
ex2asRequestsPerSec.description: Requests/sec is the number of HTTP requests that are received from the client via ASP.NET per second.

ex2asSearchCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asSearchCommandsPerSec
ex2asSearchCommandsPerSec.description: Search Commands/sec is the number of Search commands that are processed each second. This counter represents the total number of global address list, document library and mailbox searches that are issued by the client.

ex2asSearchTotal.name: ex2asSearchTotal
ex2asSearchTotal.description: Search Total is the total number of Search requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asSendMailCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asSendMailCommandsPerSec
ex2asSendMailCommandsPerSec.description: Send Mail Commands/sec is the number of SendMail commands that are processed per second.

ex2asSendMailTotal.name: ex2asSendMailTotal
ex2asSendMailTotal.description: Send Mail Total is the total number of SendMail commands that are processed.

ex2asSettingsCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asSettingsCommandsPerSec
ex2asSettingsCommandsPerSec.description: Settings Commands/sec is the number of Settings commands that are processed each second.

ex2asSettingsTotal.name: ex2asSettingsTotal
ex2asSettingsTotal.description: Settings Total is the total number of Settings commands that have been received since the service was started.

ex2asSmartForwardCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asSmartForwardCommandsPerSec
ex2asSmartForwardCommandsPerSec.description: Smart Forward Commands/sec is the number of SmartForward commands that are processed each second. Clients use this command to forward items without having to upload them to the server.

ex2asSmartForwardTotal.name: ex2asSmartForwardTotal
ex2asSmartForwardTotal.description: Smart Forward Total is the total number of SmartForward requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asSmartReplyCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asSmartReplyCommandsPerSec
ex2asSmartReplyCommandsPerSec.description: Smart Reply Commands/sec is the number of SmartReply commands that are processed each second. Clients use this command to reply with items without having to upload them to the server.

ex2asSmartReplyTotal.name: ex2asSmartReplyTotal
ex2asSmartReplyTotal.description: Smart Reply Total is the total number of SmartReply requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asSyncCommandsDroppedPerSec.name: ex2asSyncCommandsDroppedPerSec
ex2asSyncCommandsDroppedPerSec.description: Sync Commands Dropped/sec is the number of Sync commands per second whose connection to the client was dropped before a response could be issued.

ex2asSyncCommandsPending.name: ex2asSyncCommandsPending
ex2asSyncCommandsPending.description: Sync Commands Pending is the number of Sync commands that are currently pending on the server.

ex2asSyncCommandsPerSec.name: ex2asSyncCommandsPerSec
ex2asSyncCommandsPerSec.description: Sync Commands/sec is the number of Sync commands that are processed per second. Clients use this command to synchronize items within a folder.

ex2asSyncDroppedTotal.name: ex2asSyncDroppedTotal
ex2asSyncDroppedTotal.description: Sync Dropped Total is the total number of Sync commands whose connection to the client was dropped before a response could be issued.

ex2asSyncStateKBytesLeftCompress.name: ex2asSyncStateKBytesLeftCompress
ex2asSyncStateKBytesLeftCompress.description: Sync State KBytes Left Compressed is the total amount of sync state data that was left compressed since the service was started. This value contributes to the total amount of memory consumed.

ex2asSyncStateKBytesTotal.name: ex2asSyncStateKBytesTotal
ex2asSyncStateKBytesTotal.description: Sync State KBytes Total is the total amount of sync state data that was loaded since the service was started. This value contributes to the total amount of memory that is being consumed.

ex2asSyncTotal.name: ex2asSyncTotal
ex2asSyncTotal.description: Sync Total is the total number of Sync requests that have been processed since the service was started.

ex2asWrongCASProxyRequestsTotal.name: ex2asWrongCASProxyRequestsTotal
ex2asWrongCASProxyRequestsTotal.description: Wrong CAS Proxy Requests Total tracks the total number of mobile clients that are misconfigured. These clients point to a Client Access server URL that is not in the same Active Directory site as the user's mailbox. Users must make sure that their devices are configured with the URL that points directly to the Client Access server that is located in the same Active Directory site as their Mailbox server.

ex2AssistantsEntry.name: ex2AssistantsEntry
ex2AssistantsEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'MSExchange Assistants' object.

ex2aAvgEventProcessTimeInSeconds.name: ex2aAvgEventProcessTimeInSeconds
ex2aAvgEventProcessTimeInSeconds.description: Average processing time of the events chosen as interesting.

ex2aAvgEventQueueTimeInSeconds.name: ex2aAvgEventQueueTimeInSeconds
ex2aAvgEventQueueTimeInSeconds.description: Average time (in seconds) that the event lives in the dispatcher queue.

ex2aAvgMailboxProcessTimeSeconds.name: ex2aAvgMailboxProcessTimeSeconds
ex2aAvgMailboxProcessTimeSeconds.description: Average Mailbox Processing Time In seconds is the average processing time of mailboxes for time-based assistants/sec.

ex2aAvgQueueSizeEventDispatchers.name: ex2aAvgQueueSizeEventDispatchers
ex2aAvgQueueSizeEventDispatchers.description: Average queue size of event dispatchers.

ex2aEventsPolled.name: ex2aEventsPolled
ex2aEventsPolled.description: The number of events polled by the assistants.

ex2aEventsPolledPerSec.name: ex2aEventsPolledPerSec
ex2aEventsPolledPerSec.description: The number of events polled per second.

ex2aEventsProcessed.name: ex2aEventsProcessed
ex2aEventsProcessed.description: Number of events processed by the assistants.

ex2aEventsInQueue.name: ex2aEventsInQueue
ex2aEventsInQueue.description: Events in queue is the current number of events in the in-memory queue waiting to be processed by the assistants.

ex2aHighestEventCounterPolled.name: ex2aHighestEventCounterPolled
ex2aHighestEventCounterPolled.description: Highest Event Counter Polled is the highest event counter polled from the database.

ex2aMailboxesProcessed.name: ex2aMailboxesProcessed
ex2aMailboxesProcessed.description: The number of mailboxes processed by time-based assistants.

ex2aMailboxesProcessedPerSec.name: ex2aMailboxesProcessedPerSec
ex2aMailboxesProcessedPerSec.description: Mailboxes processed/sec is the rate of mailboxes processed by time-based assistants per second.

ex2aNumberOfEventDispatchers.name: ex2aNumberOfEventDispatchers
ex2aNumberOfEventDispatchers.description: The current number of event dispatchers in memory.

ex2aNumberOfFailEventDispatchers.name: ex2aNumberOfFailEventDispatchers
ex2aNumberOfFailEventDispatchers.description: The number of event dispatchers that are in failed state.

ex2aNumberOfHandledExceptions.name: ex2aNumberOfHandledExceptions
ex2aNumberOfHandledExceptions.description: The number of CLR exceptions handled by the code.

ex2aNumberOfThreadsUsed.name: ex2aNumberOfThreadsUsed
ex2aNumberOfThreadsUsed.description: Number of Threads used from the CLR thread pool.

ex2aNumberEventsProcessPerSecond.name: ex2aNumberEventsProcessPerSecond
ex2aNumberEventsProcessPerSecond.description: The number of events processed per second.

ex2aPercentageFailEventDispatchr.name: ex2aPercentageFailEventDispatchr
ex2aPercentageFailEventDispatchr.description: Percentage of Failed Event Dispatchers is the percentage of Event Dispatchers that are in failure mode.

ex2aPercentageOfInterestingEvent.name: ex2aPercentageOfInterestingEvent
ex2aPercentageOfInterestingEvent.description: Percentage of Interesting Events is the percentage of events generated on the database that are processed by the assistants.

ex2aPollingDelay.name: ex2aPollingDelay
ex2aPollingDelay.description: Polling Delay is the latency between when the most recent Mapi Event was polled and when the event was created in seconds.

ex2AvailabilityService.name: ex2AvailabilityService
ex2AvailabilityService.description: Performance counters for the Availability service

ex2aserAvailabilityRequestsSec.name: ex2aserAvailabilityRequestsSec
ex2aserAvailabilityRequestsSec.description: Availability Requests per second is the number of requests serviced per second. The request can be only for free busy or include suggestions. One request may contain multiple mailboxes.

ex2aserAvgNumMailboxProcessReqst.name: ex2aserAvgNumMailboxProcessReqst
ex2aserAvgNumMailboxProcessReqst.description: Average Number of Mailboxes Processed per Request is the average number of mailboxes processed per request. Some of the mailboxes may have errors during processing.

ex2aserAvgTimProCrsFrstFreBsyReq.name: ex2aserAvgTimProCrsFrstFreBsyReq
ex2aserAvgTimProCrsFrstFreBsyReq.description: Average Time to Process a Cross-Forest Free Busy Request is the average time to process a cross-forest free busy request in seconds. One request may contain multiple mailboxes. Free busy responses do not have meeting suggestions.

ex2aserAvgTimProCrsSiteFreBsyReq.name: ex2aserAvgTimProCrsSiteFreBsyReq
ex2aserAvgTimProCrsSiteFreBsyReq.description: Average Time to Process a Cross-Site Free Busy Request is the average time to process a cross-site free busy request in seconds. One request may contain multiple mailboxes. Free busy responses do not have meeting suggestions.

ex2aserAvgTimeProcessFreeBusyReq.name: ex2aserAvgTimeProcessFreeBusyReq
ex2aserAvgTimeProcessFreeBusyReq.description: Average Time to Process a Free Busy Request is the average time to process a free busy request in seconds. One request may contain multiple mailboxes. Free busy responses do not have meeting suggestions.

ex2aserAvgTimeProcessMtgSuggRequ.name: ex2aserAvgTimeProcessMtgSuggRequ
ex2aserAvgTimeProcessMtgSuggRequ.description: Average Time to Process a Meeting Suggestions Request is the average time to process a meeting suggestions request in seconds. One request may contain multiple mailboxes. This time includes time for fetching free busy.

ex2aserCrsFrstCalendarFailureSec.name: ex2aserCrsFrstCalendarFailureSec
ex2aserCrsFrstCalendarFailureSec.description: Cross-Forest Calendar Failures per second is the number of cross-forest mailbox queries that failed per second. These mailboxes require proxying to another instance of the service in a different forest.

ex2aserCrsFrstCalendarQueriesSec.name: ex2aserCrsFrstCalendarQueriesSec
ex2aserCrsFrstCalendarQueriesSec.description: Cross-Forest Calendar Queries per second is the number of cross-forest mailboxes queried per second. These mailboxes require proxying to another instance of the service in a different forest.

ex2aserCrsSiteCalendarFailureSec.name: ex2aserCrsSiteCalendarFailureSec
ex2aserCrsSiteCalendarFailureSec.description: Cross-Site Calendar Failures per second is the number of cross-site mailbox queries failed per second. These mailboxes require proxying to another instance of the service in a different site.

ex2aserCrsSiteCalendarQueriesSec.name: ex2aserCrsSiteCalendarQueriesSec
ex2aserCrsSiteCalendarQueriesSec.description: Cross-Site Calendar Queries per second is the number of cross-site mailboxes queried per second. These mailboxes require proxying to another instance of the service in a different site.

ex2aserForeignConnectorQuerySec.name: ex2aserForeignConnectorQuerySec
ex2aserForeignConnectorQuerySec.description: Foreign Connector Queries per second is the number of mailboxes for which free busy information is requested from a foreign connector per second.

ex2aserForeignConnectReqFailRate.name: ex2aserForeignConnectReqFailRate
ex2aserForeignConnectReqFailRate.description: Foreign Connector Request Failure Rate is the number of Foreign connector free busy requests failed per second.

ex2aserIntraSiteCalendarFailSec.name: ex2aserIntraSiteCalendarFailSec
ex2aserIntraSiteCalendarFailSec.description: Intra-Site Calendar Failures per second is the number of intra-site mailbox queries failed per second. These mailboxes do not require proxying to another instance of the service.

ex2aserIntraSiteCalendarQuerySec.name: ex2aserIntraSiteCalendarQuerySec
ex2aserIntraSiteCalendarQuerySec.description: Intra-Site Calendar Queries per second is the number of intra-site mailboxes queried per second. These mailboxes do not require proxying to another instance of the service.

ex2aserPublicFolderQueriesSec.name: ex2aserPublicFolderQueriesSec
ex2aserPublicFolderQueriesSec.description: Public Folder Queries per second is the number of mailboxes for which free busy information is requested from the public folders per second.

ex2aserPublicFolderReqFailSec.name: ex2aserPublicFolderReqFailSec
ex2aserPublicFolderReqFailSec.description: Public Folder Request Failures per second is the number of public folder free busy requests failed per second.

ex2aserSuggestionsRequestsSec.name: ex2aserSuggestionsRequestsSec
ex2aserSuggestionsRequestsSec.description: Suggestions Requests per second is the number of requests per second, specifically for meeting suggestions. The request can be only for free busy or include suggestions. One request may contain multiple mailboxes.

ex2CalendarAttendant.name: ex2CalendarAttendant
ex2CalendarAttendant.description: Performance counters for the Calendar Attendant

ex2caAvgCalendarAttendntProcTime.name: ex2caAvgCalendarAttendntProcTime
ex2caAvgCalendarAttendntProcTime.description: Average Calendar Attendant Processing Time is the average time to process an event in the Calendar Attendant.

ex2caLastCalendarAttendtProcTime.name: ex2caLastCalendarAttendtProcTime
ex2caLastCalendarAttendtProcTime.description: Last Calendar Attendant Processing Time is the latest time to to process an event in the Calendar Attendant.

ex2caLostRaces.name: ex2caLostRaces
ex2caLostRaces.description: Lost Races is the total number of times the Calendar Attendant processed items after Outlook already reached it.

ex2caMeetingCancellations.name: ex2caMeetingCancellations
ex2caMeetingCancellations.description: Meeting Cancellations is the total number of meeting cancellations processed by Calendar Attendant.

ex2caMeetingMessagesDeleted.name: ex2caMeetingMessagesDeleted
ex2caMeetingMessagesDeleted.description: Meeting Messages Deleted is the number of meeting messages deleted from noise reduction.

ex2caMeetingMessagesProcessed.name: ex2caMeetingMessagesProcessed
ex2caMeetingMessagesProcessed.description: Meeting Messages Processed is the total number of meeting messages processed by Calendar Attendant.

ex2caMeetingRequests.name: ex2caMeetingRequests
ex2caMeetingRequests.description: Meeting Requests is the total number of meeting requests processed by Calendar Attendant.

ex2caMeetingResponses.name: ex2caMeetingResponses
ex2caMeetingResponses.description: Meeting Responses is the total number of meeting responses processed by Calendar Attendant.

ex2caRequestsFailed.name: ex2caRequestsFailed
ex2caRequestsFailed.description: Requests Failed is the total number of failures that occurred while Calendar Attendant was processing events.

ex2ConnectionFilteringAgent.name: ex2ConnectionFilteringAgent
ex2ConnectionFilteringAgent.description: Performance counters for the Connection Filtering Agent

ex2cfaConnectionsOnIPAllowList.name: ex2cfaConnectionsOnIPAllowList
ex2cfaConnectionsOnIPAllowList.description: Connections on IP Allow List is the total number of connections on the IP Allow list.

ex2cfaConnOnIPAllowListProviders.name: ex2cfaConnOnIPAllowListProviders
ex2cfaConnOnIPAllowListProviders.description: Connections on IP Allow List Providers is the total number of connections on the IP Allow List providers.

ex2cfaConnOnIPAllowListProvidSec.name: ex2cfaConnOnIPAllowListProvidSec
ex2cfaConnOnIPAllowListProvidSec.description: Connections on IP Allow List Providers/sec is the number of connections on the IP Allow List providers per second.

ex2cfaConnOnIPAllowListSec.name: ex2cfaConnOnIPAllowListSec
ex2cfaConnOnIPAllowListSec.description: Connections on the IP Allow List per second is the number of connections on the IP Allow List per second.

ex2cfaConnectionsOnIPBlockList.name: ex2cfaConnectionsOnIPBlockList
ex2cfaConnectionsOnIPBlockList.description: Connections on IP Block List is the total number of connections on the IP Block list.

ex2cfaConnOnIPBlockListProviders.name: ex2cfaConnOnIPBlockListProviders
ex2cfaConnOnIPBlockListProviders.description: Connections on IP Block List Providers is the total number of connections on the IP Block List providers.

ex2cfaConnOnIPBlockListProvidSec.name: ex2cfaConnOnIPBlockListProvidSec
ex2cfaConnOnIPBlockListProvidSec.description: Connections on IP Block List Providers/sec is the number of connections on the IP Block List providers per second.

ex2cfaConnOnIPBlockListPerSec.name: ex2cfaConnOnIPBlockListPerSec
ex2cfaConnOnIPBlockListPerSec.description: Connections on IP Block List/sec is the number of connections on the IP Block list per second.

ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPAllowList.name: ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPAllowList
ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPAllowList.description: Messages with Originating IP on IP Allow List is the total number of messages with an originating IP address on the IP Allow list.

ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPAllowListPrv.name: ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPAllowListPrv
ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPAllowListPrv.description: Messages with Originating IP on IP Allow List Providers is the total number of messages with an originating IP address on the IP Allow List providers.

ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPAllowListPrvSec.name: ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPAllowListPrvSec
ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPAllowListPrvSec.description: Messages with Originating IP on IP Allow List Providers/sec is the number of messages with an originating IP address on the IP Allow List providers list per second.

ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPAllowListSec.name: ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPAllowListSec
ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPAllowListSec.description: Messages with Originating IP on IP Allow List/sec is the number of messages with an originating IP address on the IP Allow list per second.

ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPBlockList.name: ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPBlockList
ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPBlockList.description: Messages with Originating IP on IP Block List is the total number of messages with an originating IP address on the IP Block list.

ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPBlockListPrv.name: ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPBlockListPrv
ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPBlockListPrv.description: Messages with Originating IP on IP Block List Providers is the total number of messages with originating IP on the IP Block List providers.

ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPBlockListPrvSec.name: ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPBlockListPrvSec
ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPBlockListPrvSec.description: Messages with Originating IP on IP Block List Providers/sec is the number of messages with an originating IP address on the IP Block List providers list per second.

ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPBlockListSec.name: ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPBlockListSec
ex2cfaMsgOrigIPIPBlockListSec.description: Messages with Originating IP on IP Block List Providers/sec is the number of messages with an originating IP address on the IP Block List providers list per second.

ex2ContentFilterAgent.name: ex2ContentFilterAgent
ex2ContentFilterAgent.description: Performance counters for the Content Filter Agent

ex2ctfaBypassRecptDueRecptSafSnd.name: ex2ctfaBypassRecptDueRecptSafSnd
