ex2DatabaseTable.name: ex2DatabaseTable
ex2DatabaseTable.description: Database provides performance statistics for each process using the ESE high performance embedded database management system.

ex2DatabaseEntry.name: ex2DatabaseEntry
ex2DatabaseEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'MSExchange Database' object.

ex2dbDatabaseCachePercentHit.name: ex2dbDatabaseCachePercentHit
ex2dbDatabaseCachePercentHit.description: Database Cache % Hit is the percentage of database file page requests that were fulfilled by the database cache without causing a file operation. If this percentage is too low, the database cache size may be too small.

ex2dbDatabaseCacheSize.name: ex2dbDatabaseCacheSize
ex2dbDatabaseCacheSize.description: Database Cache Size is the amount of system memory used by the database cache manager to hold commonly used information from the database file(s) to prevent file operations. If the database cache size seems to be too small for optimal performance and there is very little available memory on the system (see Memory/Available Bytes), adding more memory to the system may increase performance. If there is a lot of available memory on the system and the database cache size is not growing beyond a certain point, the database cache size may be capped at an artificially low limit. Increasing this limit may increase performance.

ex2dbDatabaseCacheSizeMB.name: ex2dbDatabaseCacheSizeMB
ex2dbDatabaseCacheSizeMB.description: Database Cache Size (MB) is the amount of system memory (in MegaBytes) used by the database cache manager to hold commonly used information from the database file(s) to prevent file operations. If the database cache size seems to be too small for optimal performance and there is very little available memory on the system (see Memory/Available Bytes), adding more memory to the system may increase performance. If there is a lot of available memory on the system and the database cache size is not growing beyond a certain point, the database cache size may be capped at an artificially low limit. Increasing this limit may increase performance.

ex2dbDatabasePageEvictionsPerSec.name: ex2dbDatabasePageEvictionsPerSec
ex2dbDatabasePageEvictionsPerSec.description: Database Page Evictions/sec is the rate that database file page requests that require the database cache manager to allocate a new page from the database cache force another database page out of the cache. The eviction count is charged when the page is allocated and not when the previous owner of that page was actually evicted from the cache. If this rate is too high, the database cache size may be too small.

ex2dbDatabasePgFaultStallPerSec.name: ex2dbDatabasePgFaultStallPerSec
ex2dbDatabasePgFaultStallPerSec.description: Database Page Fault Stalls/sec is the rate of page faults that cannot be serviced because there are no pages available for allocation from the database cache. If this counter is non-zero most of the time, the clean threshold may be too low.

ex2dbDatabasePageFaultsPerSec.name: ex2dbDatabasePageFaultsPerSec
ex2dbDatabasePageFaultsPerSec.description: Database Page Faults/sec is the rate that database file page requests require the database cache manager to allocate a new page from the database cache.

ex2dbIODatabaseReadsAvgLatency.name: ex2dbIODatabaseReadsAvgLatency
ex2dbIODatabaseReadsAvgLatency.description: I/O Database Reads Average Latency is the average length of time, in milliseconds, per database read operation.

ex2dbIODatabaseReadsPerSec.name: ex2dbIODatabaseReadsPerSec
ex2dbIODatabaseReadsPerSec.description: I/O Database Reads/sec is the rate of database read operations completed.

ex2dbIODatabaseWriteAvgLatency.name: ex2dbIODatabaseWriteAvgLatency
ex2dbIODatabaseWriteAvgLatency.description: I/O Database Writes Average Latency is the average length of time, in milliseconds, per database write operation.

ex2dbIODatabaseWritesPerSec.name: ex2dbIODatabaseWritesPerSec
ex2dbIODatabaseWritesPerSec.description: I/O Database Writes/sec is the rate of database write operations completed.

ex2dbIOLogReadsPerSec.name: ex2dbIOLogReadsPerSec
ex2dbIOLogReadsPerSec.description: I/O Log Reads/sec is the rate of logfile read operations completed.

ex2dbIOLogWritesAverageLatency.name: ex2dbIOLogWritesAverageLatency
ex2dbIOLogWritesAverageLatency.description: I/O Log Writes Average Latency is the average length of time, in milliseconds, per logfile write operation.

ex2dbIOLogWritesPerSec.name: ex2dbIOLogWritesPerSec
ex2dbIOLogWritesPerSec.description: I/O Log Writes/sec is the rate of logfile write operations completed.

ex2dbLogBytesWritePerSec.name: ex2dbLogBytesWritePerSec
ex2dbLogBytesWritePerSec.description: Log Bytes Write per second is the rate bytes are written to the log.

ex2dbLogRecordStallsPerSec.name: ex2dbLogRecordStallsPerSec
ex2dbLogRecordStallsPerSec.description: Log Record Stalls/sec is the number of log records that cannot be added to the log buffers per second because they are full. If this counter is non-zero most of the time, the log buffer size may be a bottleneck.

ex2dbLogThreadsWaiting.name: ex2dbLogThreadsWaiting
ex2dbLogThreadsWaiting.description: Log Threads Waiting is the number of threads waiting for their data to be written to the log in order to complete an update of the database. If this number is too high, the log may be a bottleneck.

ex2dbLogWritesPerSec.name: ex2dbLogWritesPerSec
ex2dbLogWritesPerSec.description: Log Writes/sec is the number of times the log buffers are written to the log file(s) per second. If this number approaches the maximum write rate for the media holding the log file(s), the log may be a bottleneck.

ex2dbPagesConverted.name: ex2dbPagesConverted
ex2dbPagesConverted.description: Pages Converted is the count of database pages that have been converted from an older format

ex2dbPagesConvertedPerSec.name: ex2dbPagesConvertedPerSec
ex2dbPagesConvertedPerSec.description: Pages Converted/sec is the count of times per second a database page is converted from an older database format

ex2dbRecordsConverted.name: ex2dbRecordsConverted
ex2dbRecordsConverted.description: Records Converted is the count of database records that have been converted from an older format

ex2dbRecordsConvertedPerSec.name: ex2dbRecordsConvertedPerSec
ex2dbRecordsConvertedPerSec.description: Records Converted/sec is the count of times per second a database record is converted from an older database format

ex2dbSessionsPercentUsed.name: ex2dbSessionsPercentUsed
ex2dbSessionsPercentUsed.description: Sessions % Used is the percentage of database sessions currently open for use by client threads. [Dev Only]

ex2dbSessionsInUse.name: ex2dbSessionsInUse
ex2dbSessionsInUse.description: Sessions In Use is the number of database sessions currently open for use by client threads. [Dev Only]

ex2dbTableOpenCachePercentHit.name: ex2dbTableOpenCachePercentHit
ex2dbTableOpenCachePercentHit.description: Table Open Cache % Hit is the percentage of database tables opened using cached schema information. If this percentage is too low, the table cache size may be too small.

ex2dbTableOpenCacheHitsPerSec.name: ex2dbTableOpenCacheHitsPerSec
ex2dbTableOpenCacheHitsPerSec.description: Table Open Cache Hits/sec is the number of database tables opened using cached schema information per second. If this rate is too low, the table cache size may be too small.

ex2dbTableOpenCacheMissesPerSec.name: ex2dbTableOpenCacheMissesPerSec
ex2dbTableOpenCacheMissesPerSec.description: Table Open Cache Misses/sec is the number of database tables opened without using cached schema information per second. If this rate is too high, the table cache size may be too small.

ex2dbTableOpensPerSec.name: ex2dbTableOpensPerSec
ex2dbTableOpensPerSec.description: Table Opens/sec is the number of database tables opened per second.

ex2dbVersionBucketsAllocated.name: ex2dbVersionBucketsAllocated
ex2dbVersionBucketsAllocated.description: Total number of version buckets allocated

ex2DatabaseInstancesEntry.name: ex2DatabaseInstancesEntry
ex2DatabaseInstancesEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'MSExchange Database ==> Instances' object.

ex2dbiIODatabaseRdAvgLatency.name: ex2dbiIODatabaseRdAvgLatency
ex2dbiIODatabaseRdAvgLatency.description: I/O Database Reads Average Latency is the average length of time, in milliseconds, per database read operation.

ex2dbiIODatabaseReadsPerSec.name: ex2dbiIODatabaseReadsPerSec
ex2dbiIODatabaseReadsPerSec.description: I/O Database Reads/sec is the rate of database read operations completed.

ex2dbiIODatabsWriteAvgLatency.name: ex2dbiIODatabsWriteAvgLatency
ex2dbiIODatabsWriteAvgLatency.description: I/O Database Writes Average Latency is the average length of time, in milliseconds, per database write operation.

ex2dbiIODatabaseWritesPerSec.name: ex2dbiIODatabaseWritesPerSec
ex2dbiIODatabaseWritesPerSec.description: I/O Database Writes/sec is the rate of database write operations completed.

ex2dbiIOLogReadsPerSec.name: ex2dbiIOLogReadsPerSec
ex2dbiIOLogReadsPerSec.description: I/O Log Reads/sec is the rate of logfile read operations completed.

ex2dbiIOLogWritesAvgLatency.name: ex2dbiIOLogWritesAvgLatency
ex2dbiIOLogWritesAvgLatency.description: I/O Log Writes Average Latency is the average length of time, in milliseconds, per logfile write operation.

ex2dbiIOLogWritesPerSec.name: ex2dbiIOLogWritesPerSec
ex2dbiIOLogWritesPerSec.description: I/O Log Writes/sec is the rate of logfile write operations completed.

ex2dbiLogBytesWritePerSec.name: ex2dbiLogBytesWritePerSec
ex2dbiLogBytesWritePerSec.description: Log Bytes Write per second is the rate bytes are written to the log.

ex2dbiLogFileCurrentGeneration.name: ex2dbiLogFileCurrentGeneration
ex2dbiLogFileCurrentGeneration.description: Log File Current Generation gives the generation number of the current log file of an instance.

ex2dbiLogFilesGenerated.name: ex2dbiLogFilesGenerated
ex2dbiLogFilesGenerated.description: Log Files Generated represents the total number of log files generated by an instance since that instance was last initialized.

ex2dbiLogFilesGeneratedPremature.name: ex2dbiLogFilesGeneratedPremature
ex2dbiLogFilesGeneratedPremature.description: Log Files Generated Prematurely represents the total number of log files generated by an instance since that instance was last initialized and that have not been entirely filled with useful data. Under certain conditions the database engine will choose to switch to a new log file before it has been completely filled with useful data.

ex2dbiLogGenerationCheckptDepth.name: ex2dbiLogGenerationCheckptDepth
ex2dbiLogGenerationCheckptDepth.description: Log Generation Checkpoint Depth represents the amount of work, in count of log files, that will need to be redone or undone to the database file(s) if the process crashes.

ex2dbiLogGeneratnCheckptDepthMax.name: ex2dbiLogGeneratnCheckptDepthMax
ex2dbiLogGeneratnCheckptDepthMax.description: Log Generation Checkpoint Depth Max represents the maximum allowable amount of work, in count of log files, that may be redone or undone to the database file(s) if the process crashes.

ex2dbiLogGeneratLossResilient.name: ex2dbiLogGeneratLossResilient
ex2dbiLogGeneratLossResilient.description: Log Generation Loss Resiliency Depth represents the amount of work, in count of log files, that may be lost while still allowing the database file(s) to recover (with data loss) if the process crashes.

ex2dbiLogRecordStallsPerSec.name: ex2dbiLogRecordStallsPerSec
ex2dbiLogRecordStallsPerSec.description: Log Record Stalls/sec is the number of log records that cannot be added to the log buffers per second because they are full. If this counter is non-zero most of the time, the log buffer size may be a bottleneck.

ex2dbiLogThreadsWaiting.name: ex2dbiLogThreadsWaiting
ex2dbiLogThreadsWaiting.description: Log Threads Waiting is the number of threads waiting for their data to be written to the log in order to complete an update of the database. If this number is too high, the log may be a bottleneck.

ex2dbiLogWritesPerSec.name: ex2dbiLogWritesPerSec
ex2dbiLogWritesPerSec.description: Log Writes/sec is the number of times the log buffers are written to the log file(s) per second. If this number approaches the maximum write rate for the media holding the log file(s), the log may be a bottleneck.

ex2dbiPagesConverted.name: ex2dbiPagesConverted
ex2dbiPagesConverted.description: Pages Converted is the count of database pages that have been converted from an older format

ex2dbiPagesConvertedPerSec.name: ex2dbiPagesConvertedPerSec
ex2dbiPagesConvertedPerSec.description: Pages Converted/sec is the count of times per second a database page is converted from an older database format

ex2dbiRecordsConverted.name: ex2dbiRecordsConverted
ex2dbiRecordsConverted.description: Records Converted is the count of database records that have been converted from an older format

ex2dbiRecordsConvertedPerSec.name: ex2dbiRecordsConvertedPerSec
ex2dbiRecordsConvertedPerSec.description: Records Converted/sec is the count of times per second a database record is converted from an older database format

ex2dbiSessionsPercentUsed.name: ex2dbiSessionsPercentUsed
ex2dbiSessionsPercentUsed.description: Sessions % Used is the percentage of database sessions currently open for use by client threads. [Dev Only]

ex2dbiSessionsInUse.name: ex2dbiSessionsInUse
ex2dbiSessionsInUse.description: Sessions In Use is the number of database sessions currently open for use by client threads. [Dev Only]

ex2dbiStreamBackupPageReadPerSec.name: ex2dbiStreamBackupPageReadPerSec
ex2dbiStreamBackupPageReadPerSec.description: Streaming Backup Pages Read/sec is the rate of database read operationsperformed for the purpose of streaming backups.

ex2dbiTableOpenCachePercentHit.name: ex2dbiTableOpenCachePercentHit
ex2dbiTableOpenCachePercentHit.description: Table Open Cache % Hit is the percentage of database tables opened using cached schema information. If this percentage is too low, the table cache size may be too small.

ex2dbiTableOpenCacheHitsPerSec.name: ex2dbiTableOpenCacheHitsPerSec
ex2dbiTableOpenCacheHitsPerSec.description: Table Open Cache Hits/sec is the number of database tables opened using cached schema information per second. If this rate is too low, the table cache size may be too small.

ex2dbiTableOpenCacheMissesPerSec.name: ex2dbiTableOpenCacheMissesPerSec
ex2dbiTableOpenCacheMissesPerSec.description: Table Open Cache Misses/sec is the number of database tables opened without using cached schema information per second. If this rate is too high, the table cache size may be too small.

ex2dbiTableOpensPerSec.name: ex2dbiTableOpensPerSec
ex2dbiTableOpensPerSec.description: Table Opens/sec is the number of database tables opened per second.

ex2dbiVersionBucketsAllocated.name: ex2dbiVersionBucketsAllocated
ex2dbiVersionBucketsAllocated.description: Total number of version buckets allocated

ex2DatabaseTableClassesTable.name: ex2DatabaseTableClassesTable
ex2DatabaseTableClassesTable.description: Statistics for the ESE high performance embedded database management system by Table Class

ex2DatabaseTableClassesEntry.name: ex2DatabaseTableClassesEntry
ex2DatabaseTableClassesEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'MSExchange Database ==> TableClasses' object.

ex2dbtcDatabaseCacheSizeMB.name: ex2dbtcDatabaseCacheSizeMB
ex2dbtcDatabaseCacheSizeMB.description: Database Cache Size (MB) is the amount of system memory (in MegaBytes) used by the database cache manager to hold commonly used information from the database file(s) to prevent file operations. If the database cache size seems to be too small for optimal performance and there is very little available memory on the system (see Memory/Available Bytes), adding more memory to the system may increase performance. If there is a lot of available memory on the system and the database cache size is not growing beyond a certain point, the database cache size may be capped at an artificially low limit. Increasing this limit may increase performance.

ex2ExtensibilityAgentsEntry.name: ex2ExtensibilityAgentsEntry
ex2ExtensibilityAgentsEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'MSExchange Extensibility Agents' object.

ex2eaAverageAgentProcessTimeSec.name: ex2eaAverageAgentProcessTimeSec
ex2eaAverageAgentProcessTimeSec.description: Average agent processing time in seconds per event.

ex2eaTotalAgentInvocations.name: ex2eaTotalAgentInvocations
ex2eaTotalAgentInvocations.description: Total number of agent invocations since the last restart.

ex2JournalingAgent.name: ex2JournalingAgent
ex2JournalingAgent.description: Counters for the Exchange message journaling feature.

ex2jaJournalReportsCreatedPerSec.name: ex2jaJournalReportsCreatedPerSec
ex2jaJournalReportsCreatedPerSec.description: Journal Reports Generated Rate is the number of journal reports created per second.

ex2jaJournalReportsCreatedTotal.name: ex2jaJournalReportsCreatedTotal
ex2jaJournalReportsCreatedTotal.description: Journal Reports Generated is the number of journal reports that were generated.

ex2jaJournalingProcessingTime.name: ex2jaJournalingProcessingTime
ex2jaJournalingProcessingTime.description: Processing Time is the total time spent executing journaling rules and creating reports in milliseconds.

ex2jaJournalProcesTimePerMessage.name: ex2jaJournalProcesTimePerMessage
ex2jaJournalProcesTimePerMessage.description: Average journaling processing time/message base is the average time in milliseconds spent in journaling per message. This includes the time spent executing journaling rules and creating journal reports.

ex2jaMessagesProcessByJournaling.name: ex2jaMessagesProcessByJournaling
ex2jaMessagesProcessByJournaling.description: Messages Processed is the number of messages processed by journaling including those that were not journaled.

ex2jaUsersJournaled.name: ex2jaUsersJournaled
ex2jaUsersJournaled.description: Users Journaled is the number of message senders and recipients for which journal reports were generated.

ex2jaUsersJournaledPerSec.name: ex2jaUsersJournaledPerSec
ex2jaUsersJournaledPerSec.description: Users Journaled Rate is the number of message senders and recipients for which journal reports were generated per second.

ex2ManagedFolderAssistant.name: ex2ManagedFolderAssistant
ex2ManagedFolderAssistant.description: Performance counters for the Microsoft Exchange Managed Folder Assistant

ex2mfaItemsDeletedButRecoverable.name: ex2mfaItemsDeletedButRecoverable
ex2mfaItemsDeletedButRecoverable.description: Items Deleted but Recoverable is the total number of items deleted but recoverable through the dumpster by the Managed Folder Assistant since the start of the most recent schedule interval. The number includes items in both the mailboxes that were scheduled for processing during the schedule interval and any mailboxes that the administrator specified for processing. This counter is reset to zero at the start of each schedule interval.

ex2mfaItemsJournaled.name: ex2mfaItemsJournaled
ex2mfaItemsJournaled.description: Items Journaled is the total number of items journaled by the Managed Folder Assistant since the start of the most recent schedule interval. The number includes items in both the mailboxes that were scheduled for processing during the schedule interval and any mailboxes that the administrator specified for processing. This counter is reset to zero at the start of each schedule interval.

ex2mfaItemsMarkPastRetentionDate.name: ex2mfaItemsMarkPastRetentionDate
ex2mfaItemsMarkPastRetentionDate.description: Items Marked as Past Retention Date is the total number of items marked as past their retention date by the Managed Folder Assistant since the start of the most recent schedule interval. The number includes items in both the mailboxes that were scheduled for processing during the schedule interval and any mailboxes that the administrator specified for processing. This counter is reset to zero at the start of each schedule interval.

ex2mfaItemsMoved.name: ex2mfaItemsMoved
ex2mfaItemsMoved.description: Items Moved is the total number of items moved by the Managed Folder Assistant since the start of the most recent schedule interval. The number includes items in both the mailboxes that were scheduled for processing during the schedule interval and any mailboxes that the administrator specified for processing. This counter is reset to zero at the start of each schedule interval.

ex2mfaItemsPermanentlyDeleted.name: ex2mfaItemsPermanentlyDeleted
ex2mfaItemsPermanentlyDeleted.description: Items Permanently Deleted is the total number of items permanently deleted by the Managed Folder Assistant since the beginning of the most recent schedule interval. The number includes items in both the mailboxes that were scheduled for processing during the schedule interval and any mailboxes that the administrator specified for processing. This counter is reset to zero at the beginning of each schedule interval.

ex2mfaItemSubjectRetentionPolicy.name: ex2mfaItemSubjectRetentionPolicy
ex2mfaItemSubjectRetentionPolicy.description: Items Subject to Retention Policy is the total number of items subject to retention policy by the Managed Folder Assistant since the start of the most recent schedule interval. The number includes items in both the mailboxes that were scheduled for processing during the schedule interval and any mailboxes that the administrator specified for processing. This counter is reset to zero at the start of each schedule interval.

ex2OWA.name: ex2OWA
ex2OWA.description: The MSExchange OWA performance object includes counters that monitor Outlook Web Access.

ex2OWAASQueries.name: ex2OWAASQueries
ex2OWAASQueries.description: AS Queries is the total number of Availability Service queries since the process was started.

ex2OWAASQueriesFailurePercent.name: ex2OWAASQueriesFailurePercent
ex2OWAASQueriesFailurePercent.description: AS Queries Failure % is the percentage of the last 100 Availability Service lookups that have failed.

ex2OWAActiveConversions.name: ex2OWAActiveConversions
ex2OWAActiveConversions.description: Active Conversions is the number of conversions that are currently being processed by the WebReady Document Viewing service.

ex2OWAAttachmentUploadedOWAStart.name: ex2OWAAttachmentUploadedOWAStart
ex2OWAAttachmentUploadedOWAStart.description: Attachments Uploaded is the total number of attachments that have been uploaded since the process was restarted.

ex2OWAAverageCheckSpellingTime.name: ex2OWAAverageCheckSpellingTime
ex2OWAAverageCheckSpellingTime.description: Average Check Spelling Time is the average time that elapsed while waiting for a check spelling operation to complete.

ex2OWAAverageConversionQueueTime.name: ex2OWAAverageConversionQueueTime
ex2OWAAverageConversionQueueTime.description: Average Conversion Queuing Time is the average length of time, in milliseconds, that documents waited for the WebReady Document Viewing service to process the attachment conversion request since the process was restarted.

ex2OWAAverageConversionTime.name: ex2OWAAverageConversionTime
ex2OWAAverageConversionTime.description: Average Conversion Time is the average length of time, in milliseconds, it has taken to convert a document since the process was restarted.

ex2OWAAverageResponseTime.name: ex2OWAAverageResponseTime
ex2OWAAverageResponseTime.description: Average Response Time is the average time (in milliseconds) that elapsed between the beginning and end of an OEH or ASPX request.

ex2OWAAverageSearchTime.name: ex2OWAAverageSearchTime
ex2OWAAverageSearchTime.description: Average Search Time is the average time that elapsed while waiting for a search to complete.

ex2OWACalendarViewRefreshed.name: ex2OWACalendarViewRefreshed
ex2OWACalendarViewRefreshed.description: Calendar View Refreshes is the total number of times calendar views have been refreshed since the process was restarted.

ex2OWACalendarViewsLoaded.name: ex2OWACalendarViewsLoaded
ex2OWACalendarViewsLoaded.description: Calendar Views Loaded is the total number of times the calendar view has been loaded since the process was restarted.

ex2OWAConversionRequestsKBPerSec.name: ex2OWAConversionRequestsKBPerSec
ex2OWAConversionRequestsKBPerSec.description: Conversion Requests KB/sec is the total number of conversion requests, in kilobytes, that are waiting for conversion by the WebReady Document Viewing service per second. It does not include blocked items and queued items that have timed out.

ex2OWAConversionResponseKBPerSec.name: ex2OWAConversionResponseKBPerSec
ex2OWAConversionResponseKBPerSec.description: Conversion Responses KB/sec is the total number of conversion responses, in kilobytes per second, that are written to an output HTML file.

ex2OWAConversions.name: ex2OWAConversions
ex2OWAConversions.description: Conversions is the total number of requests that were received for conversion since the process was restarted. It includes the items that were rejected because they are in the Block list.

ex2OWAConversionsEndedByTimeOut.name: ex2OWAConversionsEndedByTimeOut
ex2OWAConversionsEndedByTimeOut.description: Conversions Ended By Time-out is the total number of conversions that ended because the queue timed out or the conversion timed out.

ex2OWAConversionsEndedWithErrors.name: ex2OWAConversionsEndedWithErrors
ex2OWAConversionsEndedWithErrors.description: Conversions Ended with Errors is the number of conversions that failed and returned errors without output.

ex2OWACurrentProxyUsers.name: ex2OWACurrentProxyUsers
ex2OWACurrentProxyUsers.description: Current Proxy Users is the number of users who are logged on whose mailbox access is being proxied to another server.

ex2OWACurrentUniqueUsers.name: ex2OWACurrentUniqueUsers
ex2OWACurrentUniqueUsers.description: Current Unique Users is the number of unique users currently logged on to Outlook Web Access. This value monitors the number of unique active user sessions, so that users are only removed from this count after they log off or their session times out.

ex2OWACurrentUniqueUsersLight.name: ex2OWACurrentUniqueUsersLight

ex2sidAverageDocumentIndexngTime.name: ex2sidAverageDocumentIndexngTime
ex2sidAverageDocumentIndexngTime.description: Average Document Indexing Time is the average (in milliseconds) of how long it takes to index documents.

ex2sidAvgLatencyRPCsToGetNotific.name: ex2sidAvgLatencyRPCsToGetNotific
ex2sidAvgLatencyRPCsToGetNotific.description: Average Latency of RPCs Used to Obtain Notifications is the average latency (in milliseconds) of RPC calls to the Exchange Information Store service. These calls are used to obtain new notifications for the given database.

ex2sidAvgSizeOfIndexedAttachment.name: ex2sidAvgSizeOfIndexedAttachment
ex2sidAvgSizeOfIndexedAttachment.description: Average Size of Indexed Attachments is the average size of attachments that have been content indexed since the filter daemon started.

ex2sidDocumentIndexingRate.name: ex2sidDocumentIndexingRate
ex2sidDocumentIndexingRate.description: Document Indexing Rate is the rate at which documents are indexed (number of documents successfully indexed per second).

ex2sidFullCrawlModeStatus.name: ex2sidFullCrawlModeStatus
ex2sidFullCrawlModeStatus.description: Full Crawl Mode Status indicates whether this MDB is going through a full crawl (value=1) or not (value=0).

ex2sidNumContentConversionsDone.name: ex2sidNumContentConversionsDone
ex2sidNumContentConversionsDone.description: Number of Content Conversions Done is the total number of content conversions that have been done in the filter daemon since the Exchange Content Indexing service started.

ex2sidNumCreateNotifications.name: ex2sidNumCreateNotifications
ex2sidNumCreateNotifications.description: Number of Create Notifications is the total number of create notifications received by MSSearch.

ex2sidNumCreateNotificationPrSec.name: ex2sidNumCreateNotificationPrSec
ex2sidNumCreateNotificationPrSec.description: Number of Create Notifications/sec is the number of create notifications received by MSSearch per second.

ex2sidNumDeleteNotifications.name: ex2sidNumDeleteNotifications
ex2sidNumDeleteNotifications.description: Number of Delete Notifications is the total number of delete notifications received by MSSearch.

ex2sidNumDeleteNotificationPrSec.name: ex2sidNumDeleteNotificationPrSec
ex2sidNumDeleteNotificationPrSec.description: Number of Delete Notifications/sec is the number of delete notifications received by MSSearch per second.

ex2sidNumDocumentsSuccessIndexed.name: ex2sidNumDocumentsSuccessIndexed
ex2sidNumDocumentsSuccessIndexed.description: Number of Documents Successfully Indexed is the total number of documents that have been successfully indexed since the Exchange Search Indexer started.

ex2sidNumDocumentFailDuringIndex.name: ex2sidNumDocumentFailDuringIndex
ex2sidNumDocumentFailDuringIndex.description: Number of Documents That Failed During Indexing is the total number of documents that have not been indexed since the Exchange Search Indexer started.

ex2sidNumberOfFailedRetries.name: ex2sidNumberOfFailedRetries
ex2sidNumberOfFailedRetries.description: Number of Failed Retries is the total number of retries that have failed for documents that originally failed during indexing.

ex2sidNumberOfHTMLMessageBodies.name: ex2sidNumberOfHTMLMessageBodies
ex2sidNumberOfHTMLMessageBodies.description: Number of HTML Message Bodies is the total number of HTML message bodies that have been content indexed since the filter daemon started.

ex2sidNumberOfIndexedAttachments.name: ex2sidNumberOfIndexedAttachments
ex2sidNumberOfIndexedAttachments.description: Number of Indexed Attachments is the total number of attachments that have been content indexed since the filter daemon started.

ex2sidNumItemInNotificationQueue.name: ex2sidNumItemInNotificationQueue
ex2sidNumItemInNotificationQueue.description: Number of Items in a Notification Queue is the total number of items (notifications) that are in a notification queue.

ex2sidNumMailboxesLeftToCrawl.name: ex2sidNumMailboxesLeftToCrawl
ex2sidNumMailboxesLeftToCrawl.description: Number of Mailboxes Left to Crawl is the total number of mailboxes that are left to be crawled on this database.

ex2sidNumberOfMoveNotifications.name: ex2sidNumberOfMoveNotifications
ex2sidNumberOfMoveNotifications.description: Number of Move Notifications is the total number of move notifications received by MSSearch.

ex2sidNumMoveNotificationsPerSec.name: ex2sidNumMoveNotificationsPerSec
ex2sidNumMoveNotificationsPerSec.description: Number of Move Notifications/sec is the number of move notifications received by MSSearch per second.

ex2sidNumberOfOutstandingBatches.name: ex2sidNumberOfOutstandingBatches
ex2sidNumberOfOutstandingBatches.description: Number of Outstanding Batches is the total number of batches sent to MSSearch that are still being processed.

ex2sidNumOutstandingDocuments.name: ex2sidNumOutstandingDocuments
ex2sidNumOutstandingDocuments.description: Number of Outstanding Documents is the total number of documents that are being actively indexed.

ex2sidNumPlainTextMessageBodies.name: ex2sidNumPlainTextMessageBodies
ex2sidNumPlainTextMessageBodies.description: Number of Plain Text Message Bodies is the total number of plain text format message bodies that have been content indexed since the filter daemon started.

ex2sidNumberOfRTFMessageBodies.name: ex2sidNumberOfRTFMessageBodies
ex2sidNumberOfRTFMessageBodies.description: Number of RTF Message Bodies is the total number of rich text format (RTF) message bodies that have been content indexed since the filter daemon started.

ex2sidNumRecentMoveMailboxCrawl.name: ex2sidNumRecentMoveMailboxCrawl
ex2sidNumRecentMoveMailboxCrawl.description: Number of Recently Moved Mailboxes Being Crawled is the total number of mailboxes recently moved to this database that are being crawled.

ex2sidNumberOfRetries.name: ex2sidNumberOfRetries
ex2sidNumberOfRetries.description: Number of Retries is the total number of retries that have been tried for the documents that have failed during indexing.

ex2sidNumberOfSuccessfulRetries.name: ex2sidNumberOfSuccessfulRetries
ex2sidNumberOfSuccessfulRetries.description: Number of Successful Retries is the total number of retries that have succeeded for documents that originally failed during indexing.

ex2sidNumUpdateNotifications.name: ex2sidNumUpdateNotifications
ex2sidNumUpdateNotifications.description: Number of Update Notifications is the total number of update notifications received by MSSearch.

ex2sidNumUpdateNotificationPrSec.name: ex2sidNumUpdateNotificationPrSec
ex2sidNumUpdateNotificationPrSec.description: Number of Update Notifications/sec is the number of update notifications received by MSSearch per second.

ex2sidPercentageNotificOptimize.name: ex2sidPercentageNotificOptimize
ex2sidPercentageNotificOptimize.description: Percentage of Notifications Optimized is the percentage of notifications that were optimized (marked as done without being processed).

ex2sidRecentAvgLatencyRPCUseObta.name: ex2sidRecentAvgLatencyRPCUseObta
ex2sidRecentAvgLatencyRPCUseObta.description: Recent Average Latency of RPCs Used to Obtain Content is the average latency (in milliseconds) of the most recent RPCs to the Exchange Information Store service. These RPCs are used to get content for the filter daemon for the given database.

ex2sidThrottlingDelayValue.name: ex2sidThrottlingDelayValue
ex2sidThrottlingDelayValue.description: Throttling Delay Value is the total Total time (in milliseconds) a worker thread sleeps before it retrieves a document from the Exchange Information Store service. This is set by the throttling monitor thread.

ex2SecureMailTransportTable.name: ex2SecureMailTransportTable
ex2SecureMailTransportTable.description: A table containing performance information for instances of 'MSExchange Secure Mail Transport' objects.

ex2SecureMailTransportEntry.name: ex2SecureMailTransportEntry
ex2SecureMailTransportEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'MSExchange Secure Mail Transport' object.

ex2smtDomainSecureMessageReceive.name: ex2smtDomainSecureMessageReceive
ex2smtDomainSecureMessageReceive.description: Domain Secure Messages Received is the number of domain-secured messages received by the SMTP server.

ex2smtDomainSecureMessagesSent.name: ex2smtDomainSecureMessagesSent
ex2smtDomainSecureMessagesSent.description: Domain Secure Messages Sent is the number of domain-secured messages sent by the SMTP server.

ex2smtDomSecureOutbndSessionFail.name: ex2smtDomSecureOutbndSessionFail
ex2smtDomSecureOutbndSessionFail.description: Domain Secure Outbound Session Failures is the number of domain-secured outbound session failures.

ex2sfaMessagesEvalBySenderFilter.name: ex2sfaMessagesEvalBySenderFilter
ex2sfaMessagesEvalBySenderFilter.description: Messages Evaluated by Sender Filter is the total number of messages evaluated by the Sender Filter agent.

ex2sfaMsgEvaluatSendFilterPerSec.name: ex2sfaMsgEvaluatSendFilterPerSec
ex2sfaMsgEvaluatSendFilterPerSec.description: Messages Evaluated by Sender Filter per second is the number of messages evaluated by the Sender Filter agent per second.

ex2sfaMsgFilteredBySenderFilter.name: ex2sfaMsgFilteredBySenderFilter
ex2sfaMsgFilteredBySenderFilter.description: Messages Filtered by Sender Filter is the total number of messages filtered by the Sender Filter agent.

ex2sfaMsgFilterSenderFilterPrSec.name: ex2sfaMsgFilterSenderFilterPrSec
ex2sfaMsgFilterSenderFilterPrSec.description: Messages Filtered by Sender Filter per second is the number of messages filtered by the Sender Filter agent per second.

ex2siaDNSQueries.name: ex2siaDNSQueries
ex2siaDNSQueries.description: DNS Queries is the total number of DNS queries performed by the Sender Id agent.

ex2siaDNSQueriesPerSec.name: ex2siaDNSQueriesPerSec
ex2siaDNSQueriesPerSec.description: DNS Queries per second is the number of DNS queries per second performed by the Sender Id agent.

ex2siaMsgMissingOriginatingIP.name: ex2siaMsgMissingOriginatingIP
ex2siaMsgMissingOriginatingIP.description: Messages Missing Originating IP is the total number of messages for which the originating IP could not be determined.

ex2siaMsgMissngOriginateIPPerSec.name: ex2siaMsgMissngOriginateIPPerSec
ex2siaMsgMissngOriginateIPPerSec.description: Messages Missing Originating IP per second is the number of messages per second for which the originating IP could not be determined.

ex2siaMsgThatBypassedValidation.name: ex2siaMsgThatBypassedValidation
ex2siaMsgThatBypassedValidation.description: Messages That Bypassed Validation is the total number of messages that bypassed validation by the Sender Id agent.

ex2siaMsgThatBypassValidatePrSec.name: ex2siaMsgThatBypassValidatePrSec
ex2siaMsgThatBypassValidatePrSec.description: Messages That Bypassed Validation per second is the number of messages that bypassed validation per second.

ex2siaMessagesValidated.name: ex2siaMessagesValidated
ex2siaMessagesValidated.description: Messages Validated is the total number of messages validated by the Sender Id agent.

ex2siaMsgValidFailMalformDomRes.name: ex2siaMsgValidFailMalformDomRes
ex2siaMsgValidFailMalformDomRes.description: Messages Validated with a Fail - Malformed Domain Result is the total number of messages validated with a result of Fail - Malformed Domain.

ex2siaMsgValidFailNonExistDomRes.name: ex2siaMsgValidFailNonExistDomRes
ex2siaMsgValidFailNonExistDomRes.description: Messages Validated with a Fail - Non-Existent Domain Result is the number of messages validated with a result of Fail - Non-existent Domain.

ex2siaMsgValidFailNotPermittRes.name: ex2siaMsgValidFailNotPermittRes
ex2siaMsgValidFailNotPermittRes.description: Messages Validated with a Fail - Not Permitted Result is the total number of messages validated with a result of Fail - Not Permitted.

ex2siaMsgValidWithANeutralResult.name: ex2siaMsgValidWithANeutralResult
ex2siaMsgValidWithANeutralResult.description: Messages Validated with a Neutral Result is the total number of messages validated with a result of Neutral.

ex2siaMsgValidWithANoneResult.name: ex2siaMsgValidWithANoneResult
ex2siaMsgValidWithANoneResult.description: Messages Validated with a None Result is the total number of messages validated with a result of None.

ex2siaMsgValidWithAPassResult.name: ex2siaMsgValidWithAPassResult
ex2siaMsgValidWithAPassResult.description: Messages Validated with a Pass Result is the total number of messages validated with a result of Pass.

ex2siaMsgValidPermErrorResult.name: ex2siaMsgValidPermErrorResult
ex2siaMsgValidPermErrorResult.description: Messages Validated with a PermError Result is the total number of messages validated with a result of PermError.

ex2siaMsgValidSoftFailResult.name: ex2siaMsgValidSoftFailResult
ex2siaMsgValidSoftFailResult.description: Messages Validated with a SoftFail Result is the total number of messages validated with a result of SoftFail.

ex2siaMsgValidTempErrorResult.name: ex2siaMsgValidTempErrorResult
ex2siaMsgValidTempErrorResult.description: Messages Validated with a TempError Result is the total number of messages validated with a result of TempError.

ex2siaMessagesValidatedPerSec.name: ex2siaMessagesValidatedPerSec
ex2siaMessagesValidatedPerSec.description: Messages Validated per second is the number of messages validated per second.

ex2siaMsgValidFailMlfrmDomResSec.name: ex2siaMsgValidFailMlfrmDomResSec
ex2siaMsgValidFailMlfrmDomResSec.description: Messages Validated per Second with a Fail - Malformed Result is the number of messages validated per second with a result of Fail - Malformed Domain.

ex2siaMsgValidFailNExstDomResSec.name: ex2siaMsgValidFailNExstDomResSec
ex2siaMsgValidFailNExstDomResSec.description: Messages Validated per Second with a Fail - Non-Existent Domain Result is the number of messages validated per second with a result of Fail - Non-existent Domain.

ex2siaMsgValidFailNotPermitRes.name: ex2siaMsgValidFailNotPermitRes
ex2siaMsgValidFailNotPermitRes.description: Messages Validated per Second with a Fail Not - Permitted Result is the number of messages validated per second with a result of Fail - Not Permitted.

ex2siaMsgValidPerSecNeutrlResult.name: ex2siaMsgValidPerSecNeutrlResult
ex2siaMsgValidPerSecNeutrlResult.description: Messages Validated per Second with a Neutral Result is the number of messages validated per second with a result of Neutral.

ex2siaMsgValidPerSecNoneResult.name: ex2siaMsgValidPerSecNoneResult
ex2siaMsgValidPerSecNoneResult.description: Messages Validated per Second with a None Result is the number of messages validated per second with a result of None.

ex2siaMsgValidPerSecPassResult.name: ex2siaMsgValidPerSecPassResult
ex2siaMsgValidPerSecPassResult.description: Messages Validated per Second with a Pass Result is the number of messages validated per second with a result of Pass.

ex2siaMsgValidSecPermErrorResult.name: ex2siaMsgValidSecPermErrorResult
ex2siaMsgValidSecPermErrorResult.description: Messages Validated per Second with a PermError Result is the number of messages validated per second with a result of PermError.

ex2siaMsgValidPerSecSoftFailRes.name: ex2siaMsgValidPerSecSoftFailRes
ex2siaMsgValidPerSecSoftFailRes.description: Messages Validated per Second with a SoftFail Result is the number of messages validated per second with a result of SoftFail.

ex2siaMsgValidSecTempErrorResult.name: ex2siaMsgValidSecTempErrorResult
ex2siaMsgValidSecTempErrorResult.description: Messages Validated per Second with a TempError Result is the number of messages validated per second with a result of TempError.

ex2siaMessagesWithNoPRAPerSec.name: ex2siaMessagesWithNoPRAPerSec
ex2siaMessagesWithNoPRAPerSec.description: Messages With No PRA per second is the number of messages per second that do not have a valid PRA.

ex2siaMessagesWithNoPRA.name: ex2siaMessagesWithNoPRA
ex2siaMessagesWithNoPRA.description: Messages with No PRA is the total number of messages that do not have a valid PRA.

ex2StoreDriverTable.name: ex2StoreDriverTable
ex2StoreDriverTable.description: A table containing performance information for instances of 'MSExchange Store Driver' objects.

ex2StoreDriverEntry.name: ex2StoreDriverEntry
ex2StoreDriverEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'MSExchange Store Driver' object.

ex2sdInboundBytesDelivered.name: ex2sdInboundBytesDelivered
ex2sdInboundBytesDelivered.description: Inbound: Bytes Delivered is the number of bytes delivered.

ex2sdInboundDuplicateDeliveries.name: ex2sdInboundDuplicateDeliveries
ex2sdInboundDuplicateDeliveries.description: Inbound: Duplicate Deliveries detected by store.

ex2sdInboundFailedRecipients.name: ex2sdInboundFailedRecipients
ex2sdInboundFailedRecipients.description: Inbound: Failed Recipients is the number of failed deliveries.

ex2sdInboundLocalDeliveryCalls.name: ex2sdInboundLocalDeliveryCalls
ex2sdInboundLocalDeliveryCalls.description: Inbound: Local Delivery Calls is the number of local delivery calls.

ex2sdInboundMsgDeliveryAttempts.name: ex2sdInboundMsgDeliveryAttempts
ex2sdInboundMsgDeliveryAttempts.description: Inbound: Message Delivery Attempts is the number of attempt for delivering transport mailitem.

ex2sdInboundMsgDelvrAttmptSecond.name: ex2sdInboundMsgDelvrAttmptSecond
ex2sdInboundMsgDelvrAttmptSecond.description: Inbound: Message Delivery Attempts Per Second is the number of attempts for delivering transport mailitem per second.

ex2sdInboundNumDeliveringThreads.name: ex2sdInboundNumDeliveringThreads
ex2sdInboundNumDeliveringThreads.description: Inbound: Number of Delivering Threads is the number of threads in delivery.

ex2sdInboundReroutedRecipients.name: ex2sdInboundReroutedRecipients
ex2sdInboundReroutedRecipients.description: Inbound: Rerouted Recipients is the number of delivery reroutes.

ex2sdInboundRetriedRecipients.name: ex2sdInboundRetriedRecipients
ex2sdInboundRetriedRecipients.description: Inbound: Retried Recipients is the number of delivery retries.

ex2sdInboundSucceededRecipients.name: ex2sdInboundSucceededRecipients
ex2sdInboundSucceededRecipients.description: Inbound: Succeeded Recipients is the number of successful deliveries.

ex2sdInboundTotalMeetingFailures.name: ex2sdInboundTotalMeetingFailures
ex2sdInboundTotalMeetingFailures.description: Inbound: Total Meeting Failures is the number of errors seen while processing meeting messages.

ex2sdInboundTotalMeetingMessages.name: ex2sdInboundTotalMeetingMessages
ex2sdInboundTotalMeetingMessages.description: Inbound: Total Meeting Messages is the total number of meeting messages processed.

ex2sdOutboundMapiEventWithoutMsg.name: ex2sdOutboundMapiEventWithoutMsg
ex2sdOutboundMapiEventWithoutMsg.description: Outbound: Mapi Events Without Message is the number of submitted MAPI events without message item.

ex2sdOutboundSubmittedMailItems.name: ex2sdOutboundSubmittedMailItems
ex2sdOutboundSubmittedMailItems.description: Outbound: Submitted Mail Items is the number of submitted mail items.

ex2sdOutboundSubmtMailItemSecond.name: ex2sdOutboundSubmtMailItemSecond
ex2sdOutboundSubmtMailItemSecond.description: Outbound: Submitted Mail Items Per Second is the number of mail items per second being submitted.

ex2sdOutboundTotalRecipients.name: ex2sdOutboundTotalRecipients
ex2sdOutboundTotalRecipients.description: Outbound: Total Recipients is the total number of recipients handled.

ex2StoreInterfaceTable.name: ex2StoreInterfaceTable
ex2StoreInterfaceTable.description: A table containing performance information for instances of 'MSExchange Store Interface' objects.

ex2StoreInterfaceEntry.name: ex2StoreInterfaceEntry
ex2StoreInterfaceEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'MSExchange Store Interface' object.

ex2sifConnCacheActiveConns.name: ex2sifConnCacheActiveConns
ex2sifConnCacheActiveConns.description: ConnectionCache active connections is the number of active connections in all connection caches.

ex2sifConnCacheIdleConns.name: ex2sifConnCacheIdleConns
ex2sifConnCacheIdleConns.description: ConnectionCache idle connections is the number of idle connections in all connection caches.

ex2sifConnectionCacheNumCaches.name: ex2sifConnectionCacheNumCaches
ex2sifConnectionCacheNumCaches.description: ConnectionCache num caches is the total number of ConnectionCache objects.

ex2sifConnCacheOutLimitCreations.name: ex2sifConnCacheOutLimitCreations
ex2sifConnCacheOutLimitCreations.description: Some instances of connection caches allow creation of extra connections even if all slots in cache are occupied. This counter shows number of cases when such connections were created.

ex2sifConnCacheTotalCapacity.name: ex2sifConnCacheTotalCapacity
ex2sifConnCacheTotalCapacity.description: ConnectionCache total capacity is the total capacity of all ConnectionCache objects.

ex2sifExRpcConnCreationEvents.name: ex2sifExRpcConnCreationEvents
ex2sifExRpcConnCreationEvents.description: Number of ExRpcConnection objects creation events.

ex2sifExRpcConnDisposalEvents.name: ex2sifExRpcConnDisposalEvents
ex2sifExRpcConnDisposalEvents.description: Number of ExRpcConnection objects disposal events.

ex2sifExRpcConnectionOutstanding.name: ex2sifExRpcConnectionOutstanding
ex2sifExRpcConnectionOutstanding.description: ExRpcConnection outstanding is the total number of outstanding ExRpcConnection objects. This value shows number of managed connection objects in GC heap.

ex2sifROPRequestsComplete.name: ex2sifROPRequestsComplete
ex2sifROPRequestsComplete.description: ROP Requests complete is the total number of completed ROP requests.

ex2sifROPRequestsOutstanding.name: ex2sifROPRequestsOutstanding
ex2sifROPRequestsOutstanding.description: ROP Requests outstanding is the total number of outstanding ROP requests.

ex2sifROPRequestsSent.name: ex2sifROPRequestsSent
ex2sifROPRequestsSent.description: ROP Requests sent is the total number of ROP requests, buffered for delivery.

ex2sifRPCBytesReceived.name: ex2sifRPCBytesReceived
ex2sifRPCBytesReceived.description: RPC Bytes received is the total number of bytes, received from the server since exrpc32 was loaded.

ex2sifRPCBytesReceivedAverage.name: ex2sifRPCBytesReceivedAverage
ex2sifRPCBytesReceivedAverage.description: RPC Bytes received average is the average number of bytes, received from the server in one succeeded RPC call.

ex2sifRPCBytesSent.name: ex2sifRPCBytesSent
ex2sifRPCBytesSent.description: RPC Bytes sent is the total number of bytes, sent to the server since exrpc32 was loaded.

ex2sifRPCBytesSentAverage.name: ex2sifRPCBytesSentAverage
ex2sifRPCBytesSentAverage.description: RPC Bytes sent average is the average number of bytes, sent to the server in one RPC call.

ex2sifRPCLatencyAverageMsec.name: ex2sifRPCLatencyAverageMsec
ex2sifRPCLatencyAverageMsec.description: RPC Latency average (msec) is the average latency in milliseconds of RPC requests. Average is calculated over all RPCs since exrpc32 was loaded.

ex2sifRPCLatencyTotalMsec.name: ex2sifRPCLatencyTotalMsec
ex2sifRPCLatencyTotalMsec.description: RPC Latency total (msec) is the total amount of time in milliseconds spent inside RPC calls. Note that since many threads can call PRCs at the same time, this value can grow faster than elapsed time.

ex2sifRPCRequestsFailed.name: ex2sifRPCRequestsFailed
ex2sifRPCRequestsFailed.description: RPC Requests failed is the total number of RPC requests that returned with non 0 result from the server.

ex2sifRPCRequestsFailedPercent.name: ex2sifRPCRequestsFailedPercent
ex2sifRPCRequestsFailedPercent.description: RPC Requests failed (%) is the percent of failed requests in total number of RPC requests. Here, failed means the sum of failed with error code plus failed with exception.

ex2sifRPCRequestsFailedException.name: ex2sifRPCRequestsFailedException
ex2sifRPCRequestsFailedException.description: Total number of RPC requests that failed with exception.

ex2sifRPCRequestsOutstanding.name: ex2sifRPCRequestsOutstanding
ex2sifRPCRequestsOutstanding.description: RPC Requests outstanding is the current number of outstanding RPC requests.

ex2sifRPCRequestsSent.name: ex2sifRPCRequestsSent
ex2sifRPCRequestsSent.description: RPC Requests sent is the total number of initiated RPC requests.

ex2sifRPCRequestsSentPerSec.name: ex2sifRPCRequestsSentPerSec
ex2sifRPCRequestsSentPerSec.description: RPC Requests sent/sec is the current rate of initiated RPC requests per second.

ex2sifRPCRequestsSucceeded.name: ex2sifRPCRequestsSucceeded
ex2sifRPCRequestsSucceeded.description: RPC Requests succeeded is the total number of succeeded RPC requests (ec == 0).

ex2sifRPCSlowRequests.name: ex2sifRPCSlowRequests
ex2sifRPCSlowRequests.description: RPC Slow requests is the total number of slow RPC requests.

ex2sifRPCSlowRequestsPercent.name: ex2sifRPCSlowRequestsPercent
ex2sifRPCSlowRequestsPercent.description: RPC Slow requests (%) is the percent of slow RPC requests among all RPC requests.

ex2sifRPCSlowReqLatencyAvgMsec.name: ex2sifRPCSlowReqLatencyAvgMsec
ex2sifRPCSlowReqLatencyAvgMsec.description: RPC Slow requests latency average (msec) is the average latency in milliseconds of slow RPC requests.

ex2sifRPCSlowReqLatencyTotalMsec.name: ex2sifRPCSlowReqLatencyTotalMsec
ex2sifRPCSlowReqLatencyTotalMsec.description: RPC Slow requests latency total (msec) is the total amount of time in milliseconds spent inside slow RPC calls.

ex2sifUNKFolders.name: ex2sifUNKFolders
ex2sifUNKFolders.description: UNK Folders is the current number of Folder objects. (C++ objects in exrpc32.)

ex2sifUNKLogons.name: ex2sifUNKLogons
ex2sifUNKLogons.description: UNK Logons is the current number of Logon objects. (C++ objects in exrpc32.)

ex2sifUNKMessages.name: ex2sifUNKMessages
ex2sifUNKMessages.description: UNK Messages is the current number of Message objects. (C++ objects in exrpc32.)

ex2sifUNKObjectsTotal.name: ex2sifUNKObjectsTotal
ex2sifUNKObjectsTotal.description: UNK Objects total is the current number of all objects that are derived from UNK. (C++ objects in exrpc32.)

ex2TopologyTable.name: ex2TopologyTable
ex2TopologyTable.description: A table containing performance information for instances of 'MSExchange Topology' objects.

ex2TopologyEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'MSExchange Topology' object.

ex2tpLatestExchgTopologyDisTime.name: ex2tpLatestExchgTopologyDisTime
ex2tpLatestExchgTopologyDisTime.description: Latest Exchange Topology Discovery Time in Seconds

ex2tpNumExchangeTopologyDiscover.name: ex2tpNumExchangeTopologyDiscover
ex2tpNumExchangeTopologyDiscover.description: Number of Exchange Topology Discoveries occurred in this process.

ex2tpNumberOfSitelessServers.name: ex2tpNumberOfSitelessServers
ex2tpNumberOfSitelessServers.description: Number of Siteless Servers is the number of Exchange Servers that could not be mapped to a site.

ex2TransportRulesTable.name: ex2TransportRulesTable
ex2TransportRulesTable.description: A table containing performance information for instances of 'MSExchange Transport Rules' objects.

ex2TransportRulesEntry.name: ex2TransportRulesEntry
ex2TransportRulesEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'MSExchange Transport Rules' object.

ex2trMessagesEvaluated.name: ex2trMessagesEvaluated
ex2trMessagesEvaluated.description: Messages Evaluated is the number of messages the rule has evaluated.

ex2trMessagesEvaluatedPerSec.name: ex2trMessagesEvaluatedPerSec
ex2trMessagesEvaluatedPerSec.description: Messages Evaluated per second is the number of messages the rule has evaluated per second.

ex2trMessagesProcessed.name: ex2trMessagesProcessed
ex2trMessagesProcessed.description: Messages Processed is the number of messages the rule has processed.

ex2trMessagesProcessedPerSec.name: ex2trMessagesProcessedPerSec
ex2trMessagesProcessedPerSec.description: Messages Processed per second is the number of messages the rule has processed per second.

ex2uaTotalSRLParameterUpdates.name: ex2uaTotalSRLParameterUpdates
ex2uaTotalSRLParameterUpdates.description: Number of Total SRL Parameter Updates

ex2WebMailTable.name: ex2WebMailTable
ex2WebMailTable.description: A table containing performance information for instances of 'MSExchange Web Mail' objects.

ex2WebMailEntry.name: ex2WebMailEntry
ex2WebMailEntry.description: Performance information for one particular instance of 'MSExchange Web Mail' object.

ex2wmApptmtAcceptPrDeclinePerSec.name: ex2wmApptmtAcceptPrDeclinePerSec
ex2wmApptmtAcceptPrDeclinePerSec.description: Rate of Appointment accept/decline per second.

ex2wmApptmtAttachmentEditsTotal.name: ex2wmApptmtAttachmentEditsTotal
ex2wmApptmtAttachmentEditsTotal.description: Total number of Appointment attachment edits.

ex2wmApptmtAttachmentEditsPerSec.name: ex2wmApptmtAttachmentEditsPerSec
ex2wmApptmtAttachmentEditsPerSec.description: Rate of Appointment attachment edits per second.

ex2wmApptmtDataRetrievesTotal.name: ex2wmApptmtDataRetrievesTotal
ex2wmApptmtDataRetrievesTotal.description: Total number of Appointment data retrieves.

ex2wmApptmtDataRetrievesPerSec.name: ex2wmApptmtDataRetrievesPerSec

Categorizations are created when a user creates a filtered view or performs a search. When the information store must maintain an excessive number of categorizations, performance can be affected.

ex2mbEventHistoryWritesPerSec.description: Event History: Writes/sec is rate the events are written to the event history of the mailbox store.

ex2ispActiveClientLogons.name: ex2ispActiveClientLogons
ex2ispActiveClientLogons.description: Active Client Logons is the number of clients that performed any action within the last ten minute time interval.

ex2ispAverageDeliveryTime.description: Average Delivery Time is the average time in miliseconds between the submission of a message to the public store and the delivery to all local recipients (recipients on the same server) for the last 10 messages.

ex2ispCategorizationCount.description: Categorization Count is the number of categorizations that exist in the public store. Categorizations are created when a user creates a filtered view or performs a search. When the information store must maintain an excessive number of categorizations, performance can be affected.

ex2ispClientLogons.description: Client Logons is the number of clients (including system processes) currently logged on.

ex2ispEventHistEventTrunMsgClass.name: ex2ispEventHistEventTrunMsgClass

ex2ispEventHistoryReads.description: Event History: Reads is the number of events read from the event history of the public store since it was started.

ex2ispEventHistoryReadsPerSec.description: Event History: Reads/sec is rate the events are read from the event history of the public store.

ex2ispEventHistWatermarkRdPerSec.name: ex2ispEventHistWatermarkRdPerSec
ex2ispEventHistWatermarkRdPerSec.description: Event History: Watermarks Reads/sec is rate the event watermarks are read from the event history of the public store.

ex2ispEventHistWatermarkWriteSec.name: ex2ispEventHistWatermarkWriteSec
ex2ispEventHistWatermarkWriteSec.description: Event History: Watermarks Writes/sec is rate the event watermarks are written to the event history of the public store.

ex2ispEventHistoryWritesPerSec.name: ex2ispEventHistoryWritesPerSec
ex2ispEventHistoryWritesPerSec.description: Event History: Writes/sec is rate the events are written to the event history of the public store.

ex2ispHTTPPerDAVTotalLockCreated.description: The number locks granted by the server in response to HTTP LOCK requests since service startup.

ex2ispHTTPPerDAVTotalNotifyReqst.description: The number of HTTP NOTIFY requests sent by the server since service startup.

ex2ispHTTPPerDAVTotalSubsCreated.description: The number of subscriptions granted by the server in response to HTTP SUBSCRIBE requests since service startup.

ex2ispTotalSizeOfRecoverableItem.description: Total Size of Recoverable Items is the total size in kilobytes of items retained for Item Recovery

ex2SANSPIPBytesTransmittedPerSec.name: ex2SANSPIPBytesTransmittedPerSec
ex2SANSPIPBytesTransmittedPerSec.description: Bytes Transmitted/sec is the rate at which data bytes are sent to the Domain Controller and clients by the NSPI Proxy.

ex2SANSPIPClientConnectionCount.name: ex2SANSPIPClientConnectionCount
ex2SANSPIPClientConnectionCount.description: Client Connect Count is the number of clients that are presently connected to the NSPI Proxy.

ex2SANSPIPClientConnectionPerSec.description: Client Connection/sec is the rate at which new client are connecting to the NSPI Proxy.

ex2SANSPIPClientDisconnectPerSec.description: Rate that clients are disconnecting from the NSPI Proxy. This counts normal disconnects and disconnects forced by the Proxy after a network error.

ex2SANSPIPClientReferrals.name: ex2SANSPIPClientReferrals
ex2SANSPIPClientReferrals.description: How many MAPI client Referral requests have been successfully satisfied, since the NSPI Proxy service was started.

ex2SANSPIPClientReferralsPerSec.name: ex2SANSPIPClientReferralsPerSec
ex2SANSPIPClientReferralsPerSec.description: Rate that MAPI client Referral requests are satisfied.

ex2SANSPIPCumulatClientConnCount.name: ex2SANSPIPCumulatClientConnCount
ex2SANSPIPCumulatClientConnCount.description: Total client connections made with NSPI Proxy for the life of the process.

ex2SANSPIPFailedClientConnPerSec.name: ex2SANSPIPFailedClientConnPerSec
ex2SANSPIPFailedClientConnPerSec.description: Failed Client Connections/sec is the rate at which connect operations from clients have failed.

ex2SANSPIPFailedReadsPerSec.name: ex2SANSPIPFailedReadsPerSec
ex2SANSPIPFailedReadsPerSec.description: Failed Reads/sec is the rate at which read operations from the Domain Controller and clients have failed.

ex2SANSPIPFailedServerConnPerSec.name: ex2SANSPIPFailedServerConnPerSec
ex2SANSPIPFailedServerConnPerSec.description: Failed Server Connections/sec is the rate at which connect operations to the Domain Controller have failed.

ex2SANSPIPFailedWritesPerSec.name: ex2SANSPIPFailedWritesPerSec
ex2SANSPIPFailedWritesPerSec.description: Failed Writes/sec is the rate at which write operationss to the Domain Controller and clients have failed.

ex2SANSPIPPacketsTransmittPerSec.name: ex2SANSPIPPacketsTransmittPerSec
ex2SANSPIPPacketsTransmittPerSec.description: Packets Transmitted/sec is the rate at which data packets are sent to the Domain Controller and clients by the NSPI Proxy.

ex2SANSPIPPeakClientConnections.name: ex2SANSPIPPeakClientConnections
ex2SANSPIPPeakClientConnections.description: Peak Client Connections is the maximum number of clients that have been connected to the NSPI Proxy at any one point, since the proxy was started.

ex2SANSPIPPeakWorkerThreads.name: ex2SANSPIPPeakWorkerThreads
ex2SANSPIPPeakWorkerThreads.description: Peak Worker Threads is the maximum number of worker threads the NSPI Proxy has had since it was started.

ex2SANSPIPTotalFailedClientConns.name: ex2SANSPIPTotalFailedClientConns
ex2SANSPIPTotalFailedClientConns.description: Total Failed Client Connections is the number of failed connect operations from clients. This is an accumulator counting all failures since the NSPI Proxy was started.

ex2SANSPIPTotalFailedReads.name: ex2SANSPIPTotalFailedReads
ex2SANSPIPTotalFailedReads.description: Total Failed Reads is the number of failed read operations from the Domain Controller and clients. This is an accumulator counting all failures since the NSPI Proxy was started.

ex2SANSPIPTotalFailedServerConns.name: ex2SANSPIPTotalFailedServerConns
ex2SANSPIPTotalFailedServerConns.description: Total Failed Server Connections is the number of failed connect operations to the Domain Controller. This is an accumulator counting all failures since the NSPI Proxy was started.

ex2SANSPIPTotalFailedWrites.name: ex2SANSPIPTotalFailedWrites
ex2SANSPIPTotalFailedWrites.description: Total Failed Writes is the number of failed write operations to the Domain Controller and clients. This is an accumulator counting all failures since the NSPI Proxy was started.

ex2SANSPIPWorkerThreadsInUse.name: ex2SANSPIPWorkerThreadsInUse
ex2SANSPIPWorkerThreadsInUse.description: Worker Threads in Use is the number of worker threads currently active in the NSPI Proxy. A worker thread handles receiving and re-sending data between the Domain Controller and connected clients. More worker threads are necessary to handle large numbers of clients.
